title: crabbers appetizer
directions: Soften butter and cheese to room temperature.
Mix in mayonnaise and salt.
Add crab meat.
Stir all together with a fork.

title: carol's punch
directions: Heat 2 cups water and dissolve jello and sugar.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: carrot walnut cake
directions: Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Cover and simmer 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand until raisins are plump. Drain well and cool.
Combine carrots, raisin mixture and mayonnaise.
Chill.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Bring to a boil in a large skillet.
Lower heat, stirring until butter melts and sugar dissolves.
Add potatoes, halved lengthwise. Baste with syrup. Cook until potatoes are well glazed.
Place in serving dish.

title: ravishing rice
directions: Place sausage in large skillet and cook over low heat, stirring to crumble sausage. Pour off grease. Combine the onion, celery and green pepper and set aside. In 4 1/2 cups of boiling water, combine the soup mix and rice and cook for 7 minutes. Do not drain. Combine vegetables and meat with this mixture and stir well.
Pour into large 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle top with slivered almonds and parsley and bake in a 325° oven for 25 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine dry cake mix, eggs, water and margarine until smooth. Pour half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels and milk in double boiler.
Pour over cake but not to edges.
Sprinkle chocolate chips next and then pecans.
Pour remaining batter over all.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
This cake is delicious by itself or it can be topped with French icing, ice cream or whipped cream.

title: stir-fry mustard greens
directions: Fry bacon in cast iron skillet; remove bacon, but leave drippings.
Add greens.
Cook, stirring almost constantly, until liquid has evaporated.
Season to taste.

title: bean soup
directions: Saute onions.
Brown meat and drain.
In a large pot, add all ingredients and bring to a boil, then simmer for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Dissolve
soda in
buttermilk.
Sift
cocoa
and
flour together.
Cream sugar and
oil;
add
eggs and mix well.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk to the sugar and oil.
Add water and vanilla.
Bake in 2 cake pans that have been greased and floured in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together reserving 1 small can chow mein noodles or 1/2 large can of noodles.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed well with Pam cooking spray. Top with remaining chow mein noodles.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine the butter and peanut butter.
Melt in a saucepan. Add the vanilla and powdered sugar; mix well.
Pour into a greased pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: pumpkin pudding pie
directions: Mix pumpkin and milk in saucepan.
Heat.
When just starting to boil, add beaten egg with the rest of ingredients.

title: lemon butter
directions: In top of doubler boiler, beat the eggs until light and lemon colored.
Add the juice from the lemons and finely grated rind from 1 lemon.
(You may add more grated lemon rind if you like it real lemony.)
Add butter and sugar; put pan over boiling water on the stove.
Stir to mix well and cook until it thickens, stirring constantly, until it is thick and clear, about 10 minutes or so. Pour into jars and store in refrigerator when cooled.
Keeps indefinitely.
Use as you would jelly, on rolls, gingerbread or toast.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Blend Crisco and flour, add milk.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto a greased pan.
Cook at 450° about 15 or 20 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 biscuits.

title: buckeye potatoes
directions: Mix all together, except Parmesan cheese.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all vegetables.
Mix sugar, salt, pepper and liquids together.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: holly's fruitcake cookies
directions: Dust fruit and raisins with 1 cup flour.
Cream brown sugar and margarine.
Beat in 4 eggs.
Add buttermilk, orange juice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add 2 cups flour, soda, spices, and salt.
Mix well.
Add fruit, raisins and nuts.
Drop spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 14 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar, soda and salt thoroughly, then mix salad oil, water, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix real well by hand or mixer.
Pour into 2 round pans or one long pan greased or sprayed with Pam.
Cook about 20 minutes or until pick comes out clean.

title: bierocks
directions: Thaw dough and let rise. Divide into 6 balls.
Simmer onion, fat and monosodium glutamate.
Add ground beef and cabbage; saute until cabbage wilts.
Roll dough into squares.
Lift meat mixture with slotted spoon and place on squares.
Fold edges of dough to cover filling.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
If desired, place cheese slices on top and melt for last minute of cooking.

title: chuck wagon soup("quick meal")
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil.
Turn to medium heat and cook for 20 minutes.
It is even better the second day.

title: easy pecan crunch pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy; add baking powder and continue beating.
Add sugar gradually until holds a stiff peak.
Add vanilla and fold in crumbs and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate until cool.
Top with whipped cream and refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours before serving.
(Pie gets moist as it refrigerates.)

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from Mandarin orange slices & pineapple. Slice bananas cross-wise. Mix all together.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Combine sugars, lard-butter (I use 1/2 lard and 1/2 butter) and eggs.
Mix soda and small amount of water to form liquid.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Shape into rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Cool overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: macadamia cheese puffs
directions: Mix cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Add other ingredients and spread on crackers.
Broil until light brown and bubbly.
Makes about 20 crackers.

title: hot spinach balls
directions: Beat eggs
in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except
stuffing mix.
When well blended, stir in stuffing crumbs and let stand 20 minutes.
Shape into balls between palms on hands,
using
a
rounded teaspoonful for each ball. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until hot and lightly browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender. Drain. Mash squash. Add salt and pepper. Add melted margarine, onion, soup, sour cream and half of stuffing mix. Mix thoroughly and pour into a casserole dish. Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cracker candy
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil and cover with saltine crackers. Boil butter and brown sugar for 3 minutes until frothy. Pour over crackers. Bake at 400° for 5 minutes. It will bubble. Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips. Let set 5 minutes. Spread chocolate with spatula. Refrigerate at least 1 hour; break into pieces.

title: "dutch bunny"(a big pancake)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat eggs and milk until they are well blended.
Add the flour and salt, stirring the batter until it is slightly lumpy.
Set 10-inch pie pan or skillet in oven to melt butter.
When the butter is very hot, pour in the batter and bake for about 20 minutes or longer or until the pancake is brown and puffed.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and confectioners sugar and cut into wedges.
Serve immediately as it will deflate quickly.
Serves 4.

title: country ham casserole
directions: Heat cheese, milk and salad dressing over low heat.
Stir until sauce is smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. This recipe freezes well.

title: bacon stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash mushrooms, drain.
Remove stems and chop them.
Blend cream cheese, salt, garlic, onion, soy sauce, half of the bacon, and chopped mushroom stems until creamy. Stuff mushroom caps with mixture and place in shallow pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining bacon and parsley.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine, confectioners sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Spread into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt chips with small amount of margarine.
Pour it over peanut butter mixture. Refrigerate until it hardens and cut into squares.

title: creamy taco over chips
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion. Drain.
Melt cheese and milk in a large boiler or in microwave.
After melted, add meat mixture and other ingredients.
Heat until hot and serve over chips as a dip or over taco salad.

title: cathy's quiche
directions: Cook spinach in microwave or steam on top of stove until done. Drain.
Cook pie shells in oven at 375°.
Cover edges of pie shell with aluminum foil; follow directions on package to cook pie shells.

title: cornbread cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Mix thoroughly.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients then add 1 1/4 cups regular salt; cover with water.
Stir every 45 minutes for 5 hours.
Then bring to a boil the vinegar, sugar and turmeric.
Drain squash and add to mixture.
Bring to a boil only.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.
Let sit at least 3 weeks before opening.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Cook water,
cornstarch,
sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg until thick, then add
lemon
juice.
Put apples into jars.
Pour hot mixture over top.
Process
quarts
for 20 minutes, pints for 15 minutes.
Open when needed and
put into pie shell.
Bake as you would any other fresh apple pie.

title: chewy cocoa and peanut butter treats
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
In saucepan stir together corn syrup and brown sugar until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter chips, cocoa and butter.
Stir until chips are melted.
Add cereal and stir until well coated.
Immediately press into pan. Cool thoroughly.
Cut into squares.

title: quick italian meatballs
directions: Beat egg and garlic salt with a fork.
Add milk.
Tear up bread in small pieces, add to the liquid and blend until it is thoroughly soaked.
(Add more milk if the bread will absorb more.) Add hamburger and knead until the meat and bread mixture is thoroughly combined.

title: pea soup
directions: Rinse and drain peas.
In large pot, combine all ingredients. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour until peas fall apart and soup becomes thick.
Serves 4.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Dump all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Pour into well-greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 38 to 40 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown onion and ground beef; drain. Mix all ingredients together. Cook slowly for 1 hour or cook slow in crock-pot all day.

title: steak and dressing
directions: Press raw meat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with onion.
Mix soups together and add bread (add 1/2 can milk if too dry).
Pour over meat and onion.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Hamburger comes out like steak.

title: sweet potato biscuit
directions: Sift flour.
Cut in shortening.
Add sweet potatoes and stir in milk, more if necessary, to make a stiff dough.
Toss dough on floured board or cloth and knead lightly.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with floured cutter or roll out with hands.
Bake in a 450° oven until golden brown.

title: white house seafood casserole
directions: Coat baking dish with mayonnaise.
Mix ingredients.
Place in dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry-pecan cake
directions: Reserve 1/3 cup strawberries for frosting. Combine all ingredients and beat for two minutes. Bake in three 8 inch or 9 inch cake pans or 9 x 13 inch Pyrex dish at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: angel food supreme
directions: Sift cake flour and confectioners sugar together 3 times so they are well blended and light.
In a very large bowl, beat egg whites, salt, cream of tartar, vanilla and almond extracts together until they hold up stiff peaks but are still moist and glossy.
Beat in granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, and continue to beat until it holds stiff peaks.
Do not underbeat. Sift about 1/2 the flour, sugar mixture over top of egg whites. Fold in with a downward stroke; do not stir.
Continue until all dry mixture is folded in.
Fold in the rest of the flour mixture by fourths.
Bake in an ungreased 10-inch tube pan or long, narrow, rectangular pan and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until light brown.
Invert immediately and cool cake thoroughly before removing from pan.
May be lightly iced and shredded coconut spread over.
Or serve plain with a dusting of confectioners sugar.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch skillet.
Bake at 450° about 30 minutes until done.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; allow to cool.
Break corned beef into fine pieces.
Add mayonnaise, eggs, celery and onion to corned beef.
Mix well.
Add corned beef mixture to jello mixture. Mix and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Put into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Let meat loaf stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: ruby's fried pie crust
directions: Mix this well.
The dough will be stiff; divide into eight equal balls.
Roll out on floured board.
Fill with favorite filling.
Fry in 1/2 inch Wesson oil, 2 and 1/2 minutes on each side.
Sprinkle with sugar while still warm, if desired.
This recipe will only work with Wesson vegetable oil.

title: seafood salad sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients except rolls.
Fill rolls with seafood mix.

title: baked chicken and mushrooms
directions: Cut chicken into strips and marinate in egg mixture for one hour.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs; brown lightly in butter. Transfer to 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Slice mushrooms over chicken. Sprinkle cheese over mushrooms.
Pour chicken stock over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour fresh lemon juice over casserole just before serving.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Boil the sweet potatoes; peel and mash them and measure out 1 1/2 cups for this recipe.
Stir the butter into the warm potato and then the sugar and milk.
Sift together 1 1/2 cups flour, the baking powder and salt and combine with the potato mixture.
When thoroughly blended, the dough should be stiff enough to roll out. If not add more flour until it is.
Roll dough out 1 inch thick and cut into biscuits.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 350°.
Yields 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken-pork adobo
directions: Take off the skin of the chicken and cut the meat off the bones.
Cut the chicken and pork into small cubes.
Mix the meat, garlic, vinegar, salt and pepper in a bowl and let sit in the refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Put the meat and juice into a pan and cook slowly until all of the juice is gone.
Add the margarine and brown the meat.
This is to be eaten over rice.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells and drain.
Mix in large bowl, all cheeses; add to shells.
Fry hamburger or sausage and drain.
Put jar of spaghetti sauce on top of stuffed shells and hamburger.
Sprinkle more Mozzarella cheese over top before baking.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: biscatti facile
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 egg white.
Knead for 5 minutes. Pinch off pieces of dough the size of an apricot and roll between palms into strips the size and thickness of a finger.
Beat egg white with a fork and brush each piece of dough with it.
Place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Boil can of crushed pineapple and mix jello into the pineapple. Add two cups of buttermilk. Let almost jell and fold in the cool whip.

title: hearty lunch soup
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in oil.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Top and wash beets.
Put into kettle of hot water until peel slips off them. Peel beets; slice or quarter and place in hot sterilized jars. Bring vinegar mixture to a boil and pour over beets and seal jars.

title: meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 350° for a juicy meat loaf.

title: oriental salad
directions: Break up noodles into small pieces.
Mix these ingredients together 5 hours before serving.
Add the dressing and stir well just before serving.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add margarine, milk and eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Stir in vanilla.
Divide into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured, 1 box cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick butter.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Cream together cream cheese and 3 eggs.
Add confectioners sugar.
Blend well.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
If using nuts, press into crumb mixture.

title: salad dressing
directions: Boil all ingredients except evaporated milk until thick.
Let cool down; then add evaporated milk.
Mix with mixture until all mixed in.

title: easy cheesy taters
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. (Shorter bake time equals a creamier dish; longer bake time browns the top, but is a little drier.)

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion.
Add meat and brown.
Drain grease off the meat. Mix other ingredients together in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add meat and mix well.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mixed berries with raspberry vinaigrette
directions: Wash berries thoroughly.
Combine berries and toss gently. Combine strawberry nectar, raspberry vinegar and vegetable oil. Mix well. Pour mixture over berries; toss gently.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Follow package directions until time to shape (after first rising).
Roll dough out into a rectangular shape until 1/8-inch thick.
Melt butter and drizzle over dough.
Sprinkle sugar until all the butter is soaked up.
Then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll dough up carefully.
Cut into 1/2-inch crosswise sections and place in a greased pan.
Continue directions on the package for second rising and cooking.

title: banana cake
directions: Dissolve
hot
water
and
baking soda together.
Cream butter and
sugar.
Add
egg
yolks
and mashed bananas.
Add vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and add with hot water mixture. Fold in
egg whites,
beaten
stiff.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes in an 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients slowly until sugar dissolves. Add vinegar, raisins and lemon juice. Cook until thickened.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and serve with carrot sticks, broccoli pieces, cauliflower, celery sticks, etc.

title: crescent chicken
directions: In saucepan, cook chicken breasts until tender in water to cover; drain and bone.
Tear chicken breasts into 2 1/2 to 3-inch long strips.
Cut cheese into 1/4 x 3-inch strips.
Separate rolls into triangles.
Place several chicken pieces and 2 cheese strips at wide end of each; roll up.
Place in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture of soup and milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: burger pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This will be a lot like a meat loaf.
Now take 3/4 of it and roll it out on wax paper like a pie crust.
Place it in a baking dish, about 9 x 11-inch.
Bring it up on the sides just like a pie crust.
Now layer slices of potatoes, carrots, peas or green beans in there and top with the remaining meat mixture, rolled out only smaller to fit the top.
Seal it as best you can, leaving a little crack for a small amount of steam to come out.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
(This is a whole meal, except the salad, and the flavor is really good.)
Don't forget to drain off the fat before serving!

title: maw maw's cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed. Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: pound cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat whites until stiff.
Wash beaters and then beat egg yolks and add sugar to them.
Blend in flour and evaporated milk alternately.
Fold in egg whites and add vanilla. Bake in greased pan 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 10 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown onions, garlic, bacon and hamburger.
Add vinegar, mustard and brown sugar.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add beans in crock-pot and cook all day or in a covered casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rick's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Great on ribs and chops!

title: chocolate delight
directions: Cook cake as directed; do not cool.
Poke holes with the round end of a wooden spoon (halfway, all over cake).
Drizzle sweetened condensed milk and then add caramel in the holes and on top of cake.
Refrigerate.
After the cake has been chilled, top with Cool Whip.

title: cheese delight
directions: Blend together the first 3 ingredients; pour in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch greased pan.
Mix together sugar, eggs, cream cheese and vanilla.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: brown sugar chews
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into desired squares while warm.

title: ice water pickles
directions: Cut up together the first 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle with salt. Mix. Empty a single tray of ice cubes on them.
Let stand 3 hours. Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Heat syrup to boiling.
Add pickles.
Bring to a boil again and put in jars immediately. Yields 8 to 9 pints.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour and margarine.
Add buttermilk and cheese.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Combine marshmallows and condensed milk.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Pack in loaf pans lined with wax paper.
Let stand in refrigerator 12 hours or more.
Will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in small bowl and let set before preparing batter.

title: pear relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring often.
Ladle into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Put jars in canner, cover with water and simmer for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 pints.

title: sugarless applesauce cake
directions: Combine raisins, dry fruit and water in a saucepan; cook, uncovered, until water is evaporated.
Watch carefully it doesn't burn dry.
Set aside to cool.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: Combine
first 5 ingredients;
add pecans and mix well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Yield:
About 3 cups.

title: wine jelly
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water to dissolve. Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add salt, lemon juice and sherry.
Pour into individual sherbet glasses.
When set, garnish with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds or toasted coconut, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Arrange ribs in shallow roasting pan.
Sprinkle with salt. Cover pan with aluminum foil and crimp it securely. Bake in a 350° oven for 70 minutes or until meat is almost tender, 1 1/2 hours for country-style ribs.

title: lemon muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth. Stir in egg yolks and beat until light.
Mix flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with lemon juice.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into muffin mixture along with 2 teaspoons lemon rind, mixing just until ingredients are blended

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Add rice, tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Cook, stirring occasionally until rice is tender.
Cover while cooking.

title: copper pennies
directions: Combine the tomato soup, mustard, vinegar, cooking oil and sugar.
Pour over the pepper, carrots and onions.
Mix. Refrigerate overnight.

title: summer salad
directions: In bowl blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and ginger and toss with can of chicken or turkey and celery.
Chill.
Serve in fruit halves placed on greens.
Yield:
1 cup salad mixture.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Combine
dry ingredients.
Mix alternately with buttermilk	to the
first	mixture.
Chill overnight, then place on floured surface
and
roll about 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut out with holiday cookie cutters and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400°. Decorate for various holidays.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend shortening with peanut butter.
Add sugar and cream. Add egg and vanilla.
Blend and mix well.
Shape dough into balls. Flatten with a fork.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sourdough - like beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt; mix well.
In a saucepan, heat water, beer and oil until warm (120° to 130°).
Add this heated liquid mixture to the flour mixture and blend at low speed until moistened, then beat 3 minutes at medium speed with mixer.
Stir in remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on a floured surface or with an electric mixer using a dough hook until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Cover.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Layer butter, graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips, pecans and Eagle Brand milk in this order.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, no longer.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Cut one ice cream sandwich in half.
Place 1 whole and 1 half sandwich along the short side of an ungreased 9x13 in. pan. Arrange eight sandwiches in opposite direction in the pan.
Spread half of he cool whip over sandwiches.
Swirl caramel generously lengthwise across the top.
Drizzle chocolate syrup generously in swirling lines widthwise.
Repeat layers. Cover and freeze. Remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all at once with a fork.
Fry as you would a pancake. Serve with maple syrup.

title: pork chop sauce
directions: Saute the onions and celery in the butter until the onions and celery are soft.
Add all ingredients except water and simmer 10 minutes.
Add water and simmer 15 minutes more.
Bake pork chops 1/2 hour in 350° oven.
Drain grease; add sauce and bake for 1/2 hour.

title: sweet raisin roll-ups
directions: Combine
raisins,
pecans,
sour
cream,
honey, butter, lemon rind
and	cinnamon.
Mix well.
Separate biscuit dough; roll out on lightly floured surface to 7 x 4-inch oval.
Spread 1 rounded tablespoon of filling on each. Roll dough starting at narrow end. Place
seam
down
on ungreased sheet.
Brush with the 1 tablespoon melted
butter.	Bake
at
375°	for
12 to 15 minutes. Combine sugar,
1	teaspoon butter, milk and vanilla. Stir
until smooth.
Drizzle	 over
warm
rolls.
Yield:
20 roll-ups.

title: no name pie
directions: Brown pie shells; set aside.
Mix coconut, butter and pecans in saucepan; lightly brown.
Mix in large bowl, cream cheese, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Pour thin layer caramel topping in pie shell.
Place layer of cream cheese mixture.
Layer of coconut and pecans.
Repeat layers.
Top with drizzle of caramel topping.
Freeze uncovered until ready to serve.

title: glazed pineapple ham
directions: Bake ham for 3 1/2 to 4 hours at 300°.
When ham is out of the oven and done, pierce the top of ham several times across the top with a sharp knife.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: steamed pork with szechuan preserved vegetable
directions: *Can be purchased in Chinatown markets.

title: easy punch
directions: Put sherbet in punch bowl and pour peach soda over it.
Stir until sherbet is melted.
Makes a full bowl of punch.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Place grape leaves in a pot and simmer for hours with a dish on top.
Brown ground meat and onion.
Cook rice; add to meat. Squeeze juice from whole lemon.
Mix ground meat, onion, rice, lemon juice, pignoli nuts and cumin together.
Place mixture in grape leaves and roll like a pig in the blanket.
Place in pot with 3 tablespoons of ReaLemon, butter and a crushed garlic.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: three corn casserole
directions: Mix 2 cans of corn and sour cream and melted butter/margarine in large bowl; one slightly beaten egg is optional. May add salt and pepper to taste. Pour corn mixture into casserole dish. Sprinkle corn meal/bread mix on top and fold in just until moistened. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown. Casserole will be firm but not dry.

title: pineapple carrot orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
After jello mixture cools add carrots and pineapple.
Refrigerate to jell.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: In heavy saucepan, put pineapple. Bring to a boil. Add apricot jello and mix well.
Let set until partially set firm. Stir in the buttermilk.
Let set until partially set again. Fold in the Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to eat.
Will keep several days, if kept covered.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix well.
Grease pan and fill not more than 3/4 full.
Let sit 5 minutes before baking.
Bake at 400° until brown on top.

title: good banana bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add mashed bananas, margarine and milk.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer until blended.
Fold in nuts last.
Pour into greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (check at 40 minutes).
Don't overbake.

title: lemon gelatin cake
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix well 4 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
When done, remove cake from oven and pierce with fork in several places.
This allows steam to escape and icing to penetrate.
Cover immediately with icing.

title: brisket of beef
directions: Cover beef with hot water.
Add vegetables and simmer, covered, until meat is tender, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Do not boil.
Add salt when half done; add more water if it is
needed. Remove meat from broth, slice and serve.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time. Press into jelly roll pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cut into squares while hot.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Season to taste.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dried apple stack cake
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine; add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Add milk.
Add 4 cups of flour and mix well.
Make a stiff dough; add more flour to make it stiff enough to handle.
Take a ball of dough about the size of your fist and pat it out in an 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven until brown.

title: peas and pasta(piselli e pasta)
directions: In medium saucepan, saute
bacon and onion until tender but not brown.
Add peas, salt
and
pepper.
Cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Pour
over
pasta shells, cooked according to package directions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach salad
directions: Dressing:
Combine sugar, salt, pepper, mustard, oil, vinegar and celery seed to make dressing.
Pour over salad.

title: mexican hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef, drain off any fat.
Add soups and enchilada sauce and simmer 5 minutes.
Line 9 x 13 pan with chips. Pour beef mixture over chips and top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.
Beat with beater until smooth.
Roll in ground nuts.
May be frozen.

title: honey sesame chicken with ginger
directions: Peel carrots.
Cut off tops and bottoms and discard.
Cut remainder into 1-inch pieces.
Place in small roasting dish. Lightly coat with honey and sprinkle with powdered ginger.
Place chicken on top.
Lightly coat chicken with honey and then sprinkle with powdered ginger.
Cover with sesame seed.
Finally, add 1/2 cup water and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 3/4 hours or until carrots are tender.
Excellent over rice and pasta.
Serves 4.

title: barley and mushrooms
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add barley and bouillon cubes.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 1 hour or until barley is tender.
Drain. Saute mushrooms, onions, garlic and butter until tender.
Stir in barley and spices.
Yields 6 servings.

title: nut horns
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco together until crumbly.
Crumble the yeast with the flour mixture.
Add eggs and sour cream; knead. Refrigerate for minimum of 3 hours or overnight.
Roll small walnut size balls in powdered sugar.
Bake at 375°.

title: ginger ale punch
directions: Make a syrup of the sugar and 2 cups water.
Cool and combine with the fruit juice, ginger ale and remaining water.

title: cinnamon stars
directions: In a large bowl of electric mixer, at medium speed, beat butter and 3/4 cup sugar until blended.
Beat in egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Divide dough in half; shape into disks.
Wrap in plastic wrap; refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: toasted orzo pilaf
directions: In a large, dry skillet, over medium-high heat, toast the orzo, stirring constantly, until lightly browned.
Remove from heat; set aside.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs, mix with cottage cheese.
Add sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, cornstarch, vanilla, salt and butter extract.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour
into
unbaked
pie
shell.
Bake in oven at 350° for
about
45 minutes or when silver knife inserted will come out clean.

title: hog wild party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon in large frying pan over medium heat until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Combine popcorn, noodles, cashews and cheese.
Combine butter and seasoned salt; drizzle over popcorn mixture tossing lightly to coat.
Stir in bacon.
Spoon mixture into two 13 x 9-inch pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 5 to 8 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: about 4 1/2 quarts.

title: cottage pudding one egg cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar until creamed.
Add unbeaten egg and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add sifted dry ingredients; alternate with milk.
Pour into 8-inch square pan greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add sugar and juices.
Mix well and add enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Stir in sugar, oil, zucchini and lemon rind and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, blending well.
Stir in walnuts.
Spoon into two greased loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Cool on rack at least 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool thoroughly.

title: daiquiri pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, jello, sugar and 1/2 cup water in saucepan; mix well, then blend in eggs.
Add remaining 2 cups water; stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Remove from heat; stir in rum.
Chill until mixture is cold. Blend Cool Whip into mixture.
Spoon into crumb crust.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Garnish with extra Cool Whip.
Serves 8.

title: cheerios mix
directions: Mix pudding and corn syrup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Mix well, then pour over Cheerios.
Coat Cheerios well and press into a pan.
Let cool.
Break apart and eat while warm or store in covered container.

title: chocolate chip and walnut muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix milk, vanilla, butter and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: *Can use cream of mushroom soup.

title: mexican surprise cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Place eggs, milk and cream-style corn in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add onion to mixture.
Pour in a greased casserole.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: quick-to-fix lasagna
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan, place small amount of spaghetti sauce.
Place 3 strips of uncooked noodles, lengthwise. Spread with 1/3 spaghetti sauce, 1/3 cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layering process twice.
Sprinkle Romano cheese across the top.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes. Remove cover and continue baking an additional 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Browned ground beef can be added to spaghetti sauce.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Roll in chopped pecans and shape.
Refrigerate.
Use as dip or cracker spread.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, green pepper, 1/2 cup picante sauce and cream cheese in saucepan on low heat until smooth.
Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture into each tortilla; roll up.
Place in greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Stir Velveeta and milk on low heat until smooth. Pour over tortillas.
Cover with foil.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Pour remaining picante sauce over tortillas.
Top with sour cream, if desired.

title: creamy pork chops and potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and onions in casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over potatoes and onions.
Top with pork chops.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat eggs until light colored.
Blend in sugar and mandarin oranges (drained).
Then add sifted flour, salt and soda mixture. Blend on low setting for 4 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bostick venison steaks
directions: Brush steaks with soy sauce; sprinkle with garlic salt, salt and pepper and dredge lightly in flour.
Brown steaks on both sides in hot oil in a large skillet; transfer to a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Set aside.
Drain drippings from skillet.
Add margarine.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly, to loosen particles in pan.
Stir in water; cook until thoroughly heated and pour over steaks.
Arrange onion slices over steaks; sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Cover and bake at 325° fr 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Use the 3 egg yolks and save the whites for the meringue. Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, milk and flour.
Cook until thick in double boiler.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 tablespoons water. Beat again until all ingredients are mixed.
Spread on pie and bake until brown in slow oven.

title: zippy croutons
directions: Season the dressing with the garlic.
Cut enough day old firm sliced white bread into 3/4-inch squares to make 4 cups.
Place bread in bowl; toss while sprinkling with the garlic flavored salad dressing.
Spread bread in baking pan; bake in preheated 425° oven for about 8 minutes, or stir in large skillet over medium heat for about 10 minutes, or until golden brown and crisp.
Remove from heat; cool.
Store airtight in a jar at room temperature, or they can be frozen.
Sprinkle over mixed green salads, cream soups or casseroles.

title: pineapple salad
directions: In large bowl, add crushed pineapple with a little juice, then jello, cool whip and cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Cover and put in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: ham delights
directions: Melt together butter, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Cut open dinner rolls.
Put ham and Swiss cheese on each roll.
Pour melted mixture over top of ham and cheese.
Sprinkle onion, salt and poppy seed over melted mixture.
Put roll lid on and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place the Twinkies in two rows.
Spread pineapple on top, then slice bananas onto pineapple.
Mix pudding according to package directions and pour over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: creole beans
directions: Cook onion, pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons oil until soft. Mix in tomatoes, green beans, salt and pepper and simmer 15 minutes.

title: chex party mix
directions: In small bowl, add seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce to melted margarine; mix well. Pour Chex cereals, nuts and pretzels into large Glad-lock zipper bag. Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture inside zipper bag. Shake bag until all pieces are evenly coated. Preheat oven to 250°.
Transfer mix to open roasting pan. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool and store.

title: martha ann's brownies
directions: Melt together the margarine and chocolate. Combine ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13 pan for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: amaretto cake(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Use a 10-inch spring pan.
Layer 1 bag of almond toast on its side.
Any extra, break and fill in.
Cook vanilla pudding in 1 3/4 cups of milk and 1/2 cup Amaretto.
Pour over cookies.
Layer second bag of almond toast.
Cook chocolate pudding in 1 3/4 cups of milk and 1/4 cup Amaretto.
Pour over second layer.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take sides off of pan.
Frost with whipped cream and decorate with chocolate shavings.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat first four ingredients at high speed for 5 minutes.
Mix all flour and dry ingredients together.
Fold into egg mixture.

title: baked chicken pesto
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray baking dish with cooking spray or olive oil.
Spread thin layer of pesto sauce on chicken breasts.
Roll chicken breasts in bread crumbs.
Place chicken breasts in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cottage cheese cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add cottage cheese and vanilla.
Sift and add flour, baking powder, salt, cocoa and soda.
Add nuts and chill dough.
Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 10-15 dozen.

title: hot crab souffle
directions: Dice half of the bread into baking dish.
Mix crab or shrimp, mayonnaise, onion, green pepper and celery and spread over diced bread.
Trim crusts from remaining 4 slices of bread and place these over crab mixture.
Mix eggs and milk together and pour over top.
Place in refrigerator overnight. Bake in oven at 325° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and spoon soup over top.
Top with cheese and paprika. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: kris' salad
directions: Make day before (to be eaten).
Layer in order.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: london broil marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour over London broil.
Allow meat to marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Grill on barbecue approximately 20 minutes on each side, depending on size of beef.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: In a large pot, cook spaghetti in boiling water with dash of salt and teaspoon butter added until tender. Drain and set aside.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix until crumbly and spread on potatoes.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Crumble cornbread in a big bowl. Saute onion and celery. Add to cornbread. Mix in soups. Add in remaining ingredients, mixing well. Put into a lightly greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix oil, melted margarine, sauce and salt; bring to a boil, then pour over cereal mixture which has been mixed up well.
Put in large pan in 250° oven for 2 hours and bake.
Stir about every 20 minutes so seasonings will bake into cereals.
Store in jars. Will keep indefinitely.

title: cranberry-apple punch
directions: Heat water and sugar to boiling, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved; cool.
Prepare using 3 tea bags and 2 Cups boiling water; cool.
Refrigerate all ingredients.
Just before serving, mix in large punch bowl.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Spread 1/2 of tortillas, torn into pieces, on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Mix chicken, soups, sour cream, green chiles, broth, onion and cheeses.
Spread half of mixture over tortillas.
Top with remaining tortilla pieces and finish with 2nd half of chicken mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, until bubbling.
Can be microwaved.
Freezes well before or after baking.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and sour milk. Add flour, baking soda and nutmeg, sifted together.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Yields 2 small loaves.

title: chicken-n-dumplings
directions: You will also need an oven bag.

title: yummy rolls
directions: Unroll 1 can of rolls onto bottom of pan. Mix cream cheese with 1 cup sugar and vanilla. Spread over rolls. Place second can of rolls on top. Pour melted butter. Top with rest of sugar and cinnamon. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit compote
directions: Great for using up apples or other fruits before they spoil. Combine all ingredients except sugar in a large pot and cover. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer until apples are soft. Remove from heat and let cool slightly.
Add sugar to taste.
Can be served hot or cold as a fruit drink.
(Remove cinnamon sticks.) Refrigerate unused portion.
Great for kids; eat the fruit, too. Optional:
Add dried prunes or raisins.
Try your own combination of fruits.

title: chinese style fried rice
directions: Bring water to boil.
Stir in rice.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, using a skillet, cook egg in butter and add chopped onion and the rice.
Stir until lightly browned.
Mix 1/4 cup water with soy sauce and stir into rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: pat's cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add cinnamon, soda, salt and pecans.
Roll mixture out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a small round cookie cutter.
Place one pecan half on each cookie.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
This will make a pretty, dainty cookie.
You can substitute the pecan half with a red or green cherry.

title: irish cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and spin in blender.
Keep refrigerated and stir well before serving.
Serve over ice.

title: low country shrimp boil
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Cook at a rolling boil for 15 minutes.
Lower to a medium boil; add sausage.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes, then add potatoes.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes, then add corn. Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Add shrimp; cook until shrimp turns pink and serve.

title: poor man's steak
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients. Pat mixture on a cookie sheet.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 6 squares. Roll each square in flour and brown in a large skillet coated with vegetable oil spray.
Place in baking dish and cover with mushroom soup. Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: easy croissants
directions: Note:
One egg and 1 tablespoon water, mixed and brushed on top before baking is optional.

title: wedding punch
directions: Boil tap water and sugar to make syrup.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Top bowl with floating strawberry halves. Yields 25 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, pecans and green pepper.
Shape into ball.
Roll in extra pecans.
Wrap in plastic.
Refrigerate until well chilled. Serve with snack crackers.
Enjoy!

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Cut the eggplant into 1-inch cubes.
Cook in a small amount of water on stove top or in microwave until tender.
Drain and mash. Add breadcrumbs, spices and eggs.
Form mixture into balls and either fry in vegetable oil or bake at 325° in a baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Serve with marinara sauce, cocktail sauce or salsa.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat first 9 ingredients, then add 1 cup oil and beat well.

title: granny's caramel cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Ice after cake cools.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Pour into large Dutch oven. Add all other ingredients except rice.
Simmer until tender.
Add water if needed.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: christmas fragrance
directions: Bring to boil.
Simmer to add wonderful fragrance to your home.
Add water as necessary.
(Can put into crock-pot.
Tastes good too!)

title: cheese 'n sausage strata
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add vegetables; continue cooking 5 minutes.
Drain; set aside to cool 10 minutes.
Stir together sausage mixture, cheese and bread cubes.
Place in greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Beat milk and eggs; pour over sausage mixture.
Cover; refrigerate several hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: judy's frozen caramel pie
directions: Melt butter; add coconut and nuts.
Cook until golden brown. Combine cream cheese and condensed milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Layer 1/4 of cream cheese mix in each pan. Drizzle 1/4 of caramel topping over each.
Sprinkle with 1/4 of coconut mix over each.
Repeat layers.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand 5 minutes at room temperature before cutting.
Very rich. Serve small portions.

title: soft corn shells
directions: Heat an 8-inch skillet over low heat.
Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour scant 1/4 cup batter into hot skillet; immediately rotate skillet until batter forms very thin tortilla, about 6 inches in diameter.
Cook tortilla until dry around edges, about 2 minutes.
Turn and cook other side until golden, about 2 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen tortillas.

title: peanut butter "believe-it-or-not" cookies
directions: Mix all 4 ingredients together until blended.
Spoon on an ungreased baking sheet.
Press with a fork to flatten.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Makes 25 cookies.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Beat in buttermilk.
Drop from spoon in hot grease; fry until golden brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water.
Heat milk, cheese, salt and pepper in double boiler.
Stir until smooth.
Add to drained macaroni.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla and brown sugar, then add flour, salt, baking powder, soda, oatmeal, coconut and butterscotch chips.
Form into balls and set on cookie sheet. Press down.
Bake at 350°.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix
flour, powdered milk and salt together.
Work them well. Put
yeast	and
sugar in warm water and let rise.	Mix oil
and egg;
beat	together.
After
yeast
and
sugar have risen, add all other ingredients.
Roll out and cut.
Let rise 1
hour or longer.
They double when cooked.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pink poinsettia punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serves 15.

title: the old rowena's famous bean salad
directions: Mix beans, onion, green pepper, celery and pimiento.
Bring the vinegar and sugar to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add oil, salt, Beau Monde and pepper.
Pour over the vegetables and mix well.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
It improves with time.
Serve on greens or in lettuce cups.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet and drain excess grease.
Pour in barbecue sauce and sugar and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Spray muffin tin pan lightly with Pam and press biscuit dough into each muffin tin cup.
Fill with barbecue sauce mixture and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package, drain well and stir butter into spaghetti.
Add grated cheese and eggs.
Form crust out of spaghetti in buttered 10-inch pie plate.
In skillet, cook ground beef, onion and green pepper until vegetables are tender and meat is browned.
Drain fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano and garlic powder.
Heat through.
Spread Ricotta over spaghetti crust.
Fill pie with tomato mixture. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese atop.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: hominy salad
directions: Wash and drain hominy.
Mix hominy, onions, celery, mayonnaise, celery seed and pepper together.
Just before serving, blend in the
Cheddar cheese.

title: banana wheat germ muffins(yields 12)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Combine all dry ingredients, except nuts. Blend well.
Beat eggs with milk, butter and banana until smooth.
Add to dry ingredients and blend until well moistened. Stir in nuts.
Spoon batter in muffin cups and bake until rich brown, about 20 minutes.
Serve warm with butter or wedge of sharp Cheddar cheese.

title: jabo's chops
directions: *Depends on number and size of chops.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar for 10 minutes on high speed. Add eggs (one at a time), then mix alternately with flour which has been sifted with salt and baking powder. (If self-rising flour is used, omit salt and baking powder.) Fold in coconut. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes (do not preheat oven) in a tube pan. Keep in oven until cooled. Cover to keep moist.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle 1 teaspoon salt over mixture and let stand 1 hour. Squeeze out liquid by hand.
Bring vinegar and rest of ingredients to boil for 1 minute.
Pour cooled mixture over cabbage mixture; mix well and put in meal size containers.
Freezes very well.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flavoring and buttermilk to egg mixture. Sift flour and dry ingredients in separate bowl. Add flour mixture to egg mixture little at a time. Add coconut. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Blend sugar and flour.
Blend in pineapple.
Cook in saucepan over low heat until stiff.
Add well-beaten egg yolks and butter. Cook a few minutes longer; cool.
Put cooled filling in baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Brown in oven.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with crackers and put 1/2 cup melted margarine over top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: grandmother's orange cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix buttermilk and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix in flour, orange rind and fruits and nuts which have been lightly floured.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until cake tests done.
Leave cake in pan; punch several holes in it with ice pick.
Pour on filling.
Let cake remain in pan for several hours or overnight.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add egg, vanilla and pumpkin. Sift in dry ingredients.
Add nuts and chocolate chips. Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: health confection
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls or into long rolls to slice. Chill in refrigerator.
If shaped in logs, slice to serve.
To store, keep in refrigerator.

title: veal french
directions: Cut veal into pieces, 4 to 5-inches.
Dip medallions into flour seasoned with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Then into beaten egg and parsley. Brown in butter until each medallion resembles a small omelette.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato juice, and form into balls. Place into large casserole baking dish.
Pour tomato juice over top.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes at 350°.
Cover and bake an additional 35 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until just tender; drain.
Add all other ingredients.

title: cheese pie(appetite control recipe)
directions: Mix together.
Put in nonstick pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in oven at 300° in
loaf pan for 1 hour or until cooked through.

title: bavarian kraut chow
directions: Mix all together.
Store in refrigerator for about 24 hours, stirring several times.

title: farmer's breakfast
directions: Dice potatoes and fry in oil until crispy and done.
Drain and set aside.
Place bacon in pan and fry until crisp.
Add diced onion; saute for 5 minutes and drain.
Add potatoes and peas.
Beat eggs with milk and pour over potato mixture.
Cook until eggs are set.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato crust ham quiche
directions: Step 1: Pat hash browns with paper towel to remove excess moisture. Press into 9-inch pie plate. Brush with butter. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from oven. Reduce oven heat to 350°.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Mash 3/4 cup fruit; combine with water.
Bring to boil and cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine sugar and cornstarch; add to fruit, stirring.
Cook until full boil is reached and is clear in color, stirring constantly.
Cool completely and pour over berries in pie shell.

title: crab helene
directions: Drain and chop artichokes. Add the rest and toss, being careful not to overdo Tabasco sauce.
Adjust mayonnaise to desired moistness.

title: asparagus green pea casserole
directions: Layer peas, diced asparagus, cheese and mushroom soup.
End with soup on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix sugar and Crisco like you were making biscuits.
Add flour.
Add yeast water and buttermilk. Mix well and roll.
Let sit for 30 minutes.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: italian dish
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Add pasta sauce; simmer.
Boil noodles, not too soft.
Alternate noodles, sauce and both cheeses in uncovered baking dish, ending up with Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese is brown on top.

title: sponge cake
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Beat the water with the egg yolks until they are thick, then fold into dry ingredients.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: In a medium bowl, stir creamy mustard, apricot preserves and soy sauce until smooth.
Stir in chicken, pineapple and green onions.
Serve over green salad or angel hair pasta.

title: innocent margaritas
directions: Using 1/2 of each ingredients, combine lemonade and limeade concentrates and carbonated drink in blender container. Blend until smooth. Add ice and blend until slushy and smooth. Repeat with remaining ingredients. Serves 8.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, except almonds. Place in a 6-inch flan pan.
Top with almonds.
Bake for 30 minutes and serve with crackers or toast points.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: party punch
directions: Mix orange juice and lemonade according to directions on can. Add pineapple juice and apricot nectar.
Pour some of the punch into a mold and freeze.

title: dickens christmas great cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Cream butter; gradually add sifted confectioners sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Then add flour mixture alternately with extra strength coffee, beginning and ending with flour and beating after each addition until smooth (batter will look curdled).
Fold in white raisins, seedless raisins, currants, mixed candied fruit and slivered almonds.
Spread in well-greased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake in moderate 350° oven 30 minutes.
Then sprinkle almonds on top of cake.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Simmer corn syrup and water for 1 minute and brush over top of cake to hold almonds in place and to give a gloss.
Cool cake 15 minutes in pan, then turn out on rack to finish cooling.
Cake will slice best when chilled.
Eat at room temperature.

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: Sift and mix dry ingredients together.
Add shortening, vinegar, water and vanilla.
Mix but do not beat very much.
Bake (350°) for 35 minutes or until cake breaks from pan.
Batter is very thin.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda, powder and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
In small bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add yeast and milk to dry ingredients and stir with fork until a soft dough is formed.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead briefly.
Store in tightly sealed plastic bag in refrigerator.
Use as needed.
Pat dough out on floured surface and cut with biscuit cutter.
DO NOT LET RISE AT ANY TIME.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in preheated oven at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: portofino mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple, cranberry sauce and wine.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly. Fold in nuts and turn into 2-quart dish or 9 x 9 x 2-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.
Soften cream cheese and slowly add sour cream until mixture is smooth.
Spread over gelatin.
Chill until serving time.
Yields 8 servings.
Family favorite.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, hot water and syrup.
Cook until it spins a thread from spoon.
Add nuts and cook without stirring until it turns golden yellow.
Add butter and soda; remove from heat.
Beat or stir quickly by hand and pour on greased foil.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: chili
directions: Brown turkey and beef; drain fat.
In a big pot add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with rice, macaroni or taco shells.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in salted water 5 minutes, drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soup, Miracle Whip and lemon juice together.
Place broccoli in baking dish.
Sprinkle chicken over broccoli.
Pour mixture over chicken and sprinkle with cheese, then bread crumbs. Bake until brown.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; drain.
Mix with other ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top before serving.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in butter. Remove vegetables from pan.
Make a medium white sauce by mixing flour with butter. Add 2 cups milk. Stir until thickens. Add 1 quart scalded milk, 2 bouillon cubes, vegetables and cubed cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add salt to taste.

title: barbara bush's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Beat the butter and both cups of sugar together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift and add flour, soda and salt.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and chips.
Bake 10 minutes.
(These are very good.)

title: col. harland sanders' pecan pie
directions: Pour pecans into unbaked pie shell.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over pecans.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 325° to 350° oven.

title: green tomato cake
directions: Beat together oil, eggs and sugar, then add vanilla and green tomatoes.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
(Pumpkin pie spice can be used instead of the cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg, but only 2 1/2 teaspoons should be used.)
Add to liquid ingredients. Mix well and pour into well-oiled Bundt pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fruit frostie
directions: Place peaches with juice, milk, Ricotta cheese and sugar in blender and process on high until smooth.
Add strawberries, a few at a time, blending until smooth.
Pour into tall glasses and garnish with strawberry, if desired.
Yields 4 servings; 4 cups.

title: cheddar mushroom puff
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter one side of each slice of bread; cut into thirds.
Place half of bread in bottom of well-buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with half of cheese slices and half of mushrooms.
Repeat cheese and mushroom layers. Top with bread.
Combine milk, eggs and seasonings.
Pour mixture into casserole.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until puffy and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: linguini with white clam sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, pour in olive oil just to cover bottom of pan.
Add garlic to cold oil; bring heat up slowly just until tender, then add the juices from the white clam sauce, minced clams and whole baby clams.
Bring to slow boil.
Add about 2 to 3 tablespoons of parsley to juices.
Just before you serve, add all clams to the sauce; heat about 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked linguini noodles.
Serves 4 people.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix hamburg,
onion
soup
mix and egg. Form into small meat balls. Brown
in
oven or fry pan.	Drain off grease. Put meat balls
in
crock-pot.
Mix tomato sauce, cranberry sauce, lemon juice,
brown
sugar
and
barbecue
sauce	and
heat in crock-pot.	Simmer	until ready to serve and when nearly done, add 8 or
crushed
gingersnaps.
Use as many as needed for proper taste.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve right from the crock-pot.

title: peanut butter balls(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Combine peanut butter, honey and vanilla. Blend thoroughly. Mix milk powder and oatmeal together. Gradually add to peanut butter mixture, blending thoroughly, using hands if necessary as dough will be stiff. Add boiling water, blending well. Shape in one-inch balls and roll in coconut.

title: bisquick banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch. Beat all ingredients vigorously with spoon for 30 seconds.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake until toothpick in center comes out clean, 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan and remove.
Slice, eat and enjoy.

title: chinese surprise
directions: Cook spaghetti, Chinese noodles or rice as directed.
Brown ground beef in large skillet or saucepan.
Add frozen vegetables and spices; stir-fry.
Add 1/2 bottle of soy sauce and 3 cups water; let boil about 6 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter and spread over graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Do not burn!

title: jello supreme
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to directions on package. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan and stir in pineapple.
Cover with sliced bananas and miniature marshmallows.
Refrigerate until firm.
Mix together flour, sugar, pineapple juice, eggs and butter. Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Cool thoroughly.
Add the Cool Whip.
Spread over the Jell-O mixture and garnish with grated cheese. Very good.

title: spinach salad
directions: Chill and serve over fresh salad of the following:

title: tomato cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cheeses and chilies in a bowl. Turn into well-greased, shallow glass bowl.

title: orange blossom cooler
directions: Combine frozen concentrate and water.
Put sherbet and ice cream in bottom of punch bowl.
Break into small pieces with large spoon.
Add juice mixtures.
Stir until sherbet and ice cream are partially melted. Makes about 5 quarts punch or 40 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: vidalia onions
directions: Sprinkle garlic salt in onion hole.
Place in broiler proof baking dish.
Put about 1/2-inch water in dish.
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 60 minutes.
With about 10 to 15 minutes left, add margarine (about 1 teaspoon) to holes and fill with cheese. Return to oven to brown.
Keep adding Parmesan cheese as it melts. Turn on broiler and place onions under it until they brown.

title: baked new potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and place in shallow greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, cheese and bacon.
Drizzle with butter.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts (about 10 minutes).

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Add taco seasoning. In a saucepan, mix mushroom soup and water.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fourteen special ingredients
directions: Cut fruits into 1/4-inch cubes.
Place remaining ingredients, except almond extract, in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add the fruits and simmer 2 minutes.
Stir in the almond flavoring.
Pour into a bowl and refrigerate for 2 hours.
This recipe can be doubled and unused portion stored in the refrigerator for several weeks to use as a garnish or side dish.
Serve as a dessert or as a side dish with Far East cuisine.
Serves 4.

title: english trifle
directions: Drain fruit and reserve juice.
Break jelly rolls into pieces (if using cake and jam, break cake into pieces and spread with jam).
Put into a 4-pint glass bowl.
Sprinkle with some of fruit juice and the sherry.
Give everything a good stir to soak up the liquid.
Cake should be nicely dampened.
Place fruit on top of cake.
Make custard.
Allow to cool slightly.
Stir frequently to prevent skin forming.
Pour over fruit.
Chill until firm.
Whip the cream, using spoon of sugar and spread evenly over custard. Sprinkle with grated chocolate.

title: oatmeal apple muffins
directions: Combine.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Brown chuck and onion.
Pour off excess fat, set aside.
In small bowl, mix tomato soup with 1 can water.
In large casserole dish, cover bottom with 1/2 of the cabbage, then the cooked rice, then ground meat.
Add 1/2 of the tomato mixture and remaining cabbage.
Finish with the remaining tomato mixture, cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in moderate oven until cabbage is tender, about 45 minutes.
Tastes like cabbage rolls without the work.

title: old green tomato ketchup
directions: Mix and let stand for 2 hours.
Place in bag and drain overnight.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3 tablespoons warm water. Mix sugar, margarine, 1 cup water, eggs and salt. Add yeast and flour; refrigerate overnight. From 3 to 5 hours before baking, divide dough in half. Roll each half in big pie shape.
Spread with warm melted margarine. Cut into 16 wedges. Roll from big to little end. Bake 5 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Mix crumbs and paprika.
Coat chicken pieces with milk, then crumb mixture.
Place coated chicken pieces in casserole dish with meatiest portions toward outside of dish.
Cook for approximately 1 hour or until well done at 375°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Add juices and sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in candied fruit, nuts and pineapple, mixing thoroughly.
Bake in a large pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours until done.

title: easy rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix cake according to the package.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread rhubarb over batter.
Sprinkle with sugar and pour cream over the top.
Layer, don't mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until it tests done.

title: waldorf chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Stir together, flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Add water, vanilla and mayonnaise. Beat at low speed until smooth.

Turn into two greased and waxpaper lined 8 inch layer cake pans, or 1 greased and floured 9 inch square pan. Bake 30 minutes for 8 inch pans and 45 minutes for 9 inch pan. Cool completely before frosting.

title: strawberries with fluffy cream cheese dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar, and vanilla at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream; serve with berries.

title: time to spare spuds
directions: Cut hot potatoes in half lengthwise; carefully scoop out pulp, leaving a thin shell.
In a bowl, mash pulp until smooth. Beat in sour cream, cheese, onion, milk, butter, parsley and salt. Fill shells; brush with butter.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: beef kabobs with vegetables
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in shallow container.
Add meat. Cover and marinate 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Parboil onions 10 minutes; drain well and set aside.
Remove meat from marinade, reserving marinade.
Alternate meat and vegetables on skewers. Grill kabobs over medium-hot coals 7 to 8 minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness, turning and basting frequently with reserved marinade.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cherries and chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Spread with melted butter, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered. Mix chili sauce, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes longer.
Add cherries and sherry and bake another 30 minutes.

title: mushroom tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti as label suggests.
Cut cheese into small pieces.
In 3-quart saucepan, over medium heat, melt oleo and cook mushrooms and onion until tender (5 minutes).
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended.
Gradually stir in milk and sherry.
Add cheese and parsley.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Place hot spaghetti in ovenproof dish.
Pour sauce over spaghetti. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until lightly brown on top.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across the grain into very thin strips.
In skillet, over high heat, in butter, cook the beef and the onion until beef is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Set aside. Stir in soup and paprika.
Heat through, stirring occasionally. Reduce to very low heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Gently heat through.
Serve over noodles.

title: california marinade
directions: Shake in large bottle.
Use to marinate chicken, shrimp or beef before grilling.
Great for shish kabobs!

title: best ever cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar, continue, adding eggs, one at a time, along with oil and vanilla.
Sift together the remaining ingredients, then add mixture, a third at a time and mix well. Drop by teaspoons on oiled cookie sheet and press down with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together all but last 2 ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and chopped nuts over cake before baking.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: bierox
directions: Heat 20 minutes.
Make crescent rolls in squares.
Fold in corners in muffin pans.

title: confetti salsa
directions: Coarsely chop tomatoes and fresh peppers.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Makes about 5 cups.
Serve in clear glass bowl to best enjoy colorful appearance of salsa.
Serve as appetizer with tortilla chips.
Great with any Mexican food or as flavorful side dish to any meat.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time and beat.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add buttermilk; mix well.
Add nuts, raisins and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mom's corn bread stuffing
directions: Prepare corn bread using package directions.
Cool.
Crumble into bowl.
Add cubed bread, broth, butter, celery, onion, eggs, salt and pepper; mix well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: chocolate fudge syrup
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa on the stove for 1 minute.
Add 1/2 stick butter.
When melted add 1 small can of Pet milk and boil for 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Good served with plain cake and vanilla ice cream.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Mix milk, Bisquick and cheese about 30 seconds.
Drop dough on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 3 to 10 minutes at 450°.
Mix garlic and butter.
Brush on cooked biscuits.

title: angels dessert
directions: Combine all together and put in well greased angel cake pan or bundt pan and chill. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directions state.
Pour into 3 sprayed cake pans.
Cook on 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until done.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine water, rice and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add sugar and milk.
On medium heat, bring to a boil.
Turn off heat.
Stir in egg, beating quickly. Add vanilla.
Cover and refrigerate until cool.
Serve with nutmeg.
If you need pudding to set more quickly, cut the milk down to 3 to 3 1/2 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter and add ingredients in order.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° for 40 minutes longer.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling point.
Mix in the jello while hot. Allow this to cool.
Add 1 cup buttermilk to blend.
Add the other cup of buttermilk and the 8 ounce carton of Cool Whip.
Mold and refrigerate.
Serves 10 people.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse.
Combine with chopped ingredients.
Add Italian dressing (I use Kraft Zesty Italian) and 1 bottle McCormick Salad Supreme (maybe a little less).
Toss and refrigerate.
This will keep for several days.
Great for cookouts.

title: baked chicken with cranberry marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass dish.
Marinate 2 hours or longer in refrigerator.
To bake, arrange chicken pieces in a single layer in a large, buttered baking dish.
Pour marinade over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting frequently.
Transfer chicken to serving dish.
Cover and keep warm.
Simmer pan juices to reduce slightly.
Serve over warm chicken.

title: pan fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken and let drain. Mix eggs and milk in a bowl. Sift flour, pancake flour, pepper and salt in a dish. Dip chicken in egg and milk mixture, roll in flour mixture. Place in covered skillet and fry until brown, turning about every 15 minutes. (Skillet should be heated to 350°, be sure and fry until tender about 45 minutes). She used an electric skillet.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Cut oleo into the flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Make a well in the center. Add buttermilk. Stir until dough clings together.
On a lightly floured surface, knead dough for 10 to 12 strokes. Roll dough to a 12 x 16-inch rectangle. Sprinkle sausage evenly atop dough.
Roll up, jelly roll style, starting from one of the long sides. Slice into 1-inch thick slices.
Place, cut side down, on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake in a 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve hot with honey or molasses.
Makes 16!

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together except cheese and potato chips and put in a casserole dish.
Put sharp cheese and crushed potato chips on top. Mix up the night before.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: california apricot power bars(healthy!  healthy!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with foil.
In large bowl, stir together apricots, pecans and dates; divide in half.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to half of fruit-nut mixture; toss to coat.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, brown sugar, apple juice and vanilla; stir into flour mixture until thoroughly moistened.
Spread batter evenly into prepared pan.
