Lightly press remaining fruit-nut mixture on top.

title: perfect brownies
directions: Melt chocolate thoroughly; cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in chocolate (melted) or cocoa, vanilla and flour.
Add nuts into batter or sprinkle on top after batter is poured in pan.
Pour batter into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with Fudge Frosting and sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: apricot lemon velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine all ingredients in large bowl and beat until well mixed. Pour into a 9x13x2 inch baking pan that has been greased and lightly floured on bottom only. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of cake.
Remove from oven and allow to cool completely before adding the icing.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs and milk. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Stir in apples and nuts. Pour into greased and floured loaf pans. Top with the following topping.

title: chinese mixed vegetables
directions: Preheat wok or frying pan.
Add oil and swirl around.
Rub bottom and sides with ginger.
Discard ginger.
Add vegetables; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add garlic, sesame oil and chicken broth. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 4 minutes.
Remove cover.
Add cabbage, mushrooms and cornstarch, dissolved in 1 tablespoon water.
Cook, stirring until sauce is clear and thickened.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coquilles st. jaques, mornay
directions: Saute scallops in 1 ounce butter for 1 minute.
Add lemon juice.
Remove scallops and place in coquilles (shells).
Keep warm.
Saute shallots and sliced mushrooms in remaining butter; add wine and liquid from scallops.
Reduce 1/3.
Add hot cream sauce.
Blend in liaison.
Season to taste.
Do not boil.
Pour sauce over scallops.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Brown under broiler. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Place rhubarb, sugar, oil, milk, and eggs in blender, process until smooth.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in large bowl.
Stir well.
Add rhubarb mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour - or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let cool in pans 10 minutes - remove from pans and cool on rack.

title: homemade amaretto
directions: Combine sugar, water and lemon peel in pot and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add vodka and extracts. Enjoy!

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients but almonds and cornflakes.
Sprinkle these on top and drizzle butter on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes covered at 300°.
Uncover and brown.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine beaten egg, milk and melted shortening.
Add to the dry ingredients.
Beat until mixture is smooth.
Stir in washed blueberries. Drop batter from a tablespoon onto a hot griddle. Cook one side until puffed, full of bubbles, and cooked on the edges.
Turn and cook on the other side.
Makes about 10 (3-inch) cakes.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Warm in microwave 2 minutes. Stir, turn bowl and microwave 2 minutes more until bubbly.
Serve with any fresh fruit.

title: wet burritos
directions: In skillet used for browning beef, cook beef and taco seasoning according to directions on seasoning packet; simmer.
In saucepan, mix chili, Cheez Whiz, sour cream and 1 tablespoon shredded cheese; simmer.

title: italian sausage soup(serves 4)
directions: Cut up sausage and cook until done.
Drain fat by placing sausage on paper towels.
In a large Dutch oven or soup pot, combine all ingredients, except pasta.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Add dry pasta and cook until tender.
Ladle into bowls, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: sausage breakfast
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat until done, stirring to crumble well.
Drain sausage on paper towels and set aside.

title: church window candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine, stirring occasionally. Let cool 5 minutes.
Mix in marshmallows and nuts slightly and cool 15 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on waxed paper.
Pour mixture so it resembles a log, then cool again for 15 minutes.
Roll mixture in coconut until the log is covered.
Wrap log in waxed paper and chill 24 hours.
Cut into slices.
Candy will resemble stained glass windows.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Fry bacon. After all bacon is done, fry onion and cabbage in the bacon grease. Cook egg noodles; drain. Add your cabbage, onion and bacon grease to noodles. Tear or cut bacon up and add. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a saucepan; blend well. Gradually add water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Bring mixture to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve hot over cake.
Store in refrigerator.
Heat as needed.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: chicken stew in a crock-pot
directions: The ingredients are geared toward how many people you are serving.
Smaller amounts for a few people and larger amounts for a big family.
Place all ingredients, including the cans of soup into a crock-pot early in the day.
Be sure to cut up the chicken into smaller pieces.
Turn the crock-pot on low for 6 to 8 hours and you will have a delicious, easy supper.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Mix all together after cooked.

title: gazpacho(soup)
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve with croutons.

title: mousse in a minute
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on package, using only 1 1/2 cups milk.
Fold in whipped topping and spoon into dessert dishes or 6 ounce Ready-Crust graham cracker pie crust.
Garnish with additional whipped topping if desired.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Gradually beat flour mix into egg mix.
Fold in nuts and zucchini.
Cover and chill.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by teaspoon 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes, until nicely browned and glazed on top.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter and flour together. Add eggs 1 at a time and continue to cream. Add milk and mix well, then add vanilla. Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add butter and mix like pie crust.
Add egg mixed with milk.
Pat into pan, 11 x 8 1/2-inches.
Put rhubarb over sugar and jello, then add Streusel over top.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: In mixing bowl combine pumpkin, sugar, cornstarch, salt, ginger and cinnamon.
Blend in molasses, eggs and milk.
Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Bake at 425° to 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pudding graham cake
directions: Try also with banana cream pudding and strawberry frosting.

title: cream cheese pound cake(state fair blue ribbon winning recipe)
directions: In small bowl, mix flour, soda and salt.
In large mixing bowl, cream together the margarine, Crisco, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Slowly add flour mixture to mixture in large bowl.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop in small balls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: gentlemen's delight!
directions: Mix first two ingredients together and press in 9 x 13-inch pan (saving some to sprinkle on top).
Mix pudding and milk, then stir in the ice cream.
Spread over the crackers and top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with saved crackers and it's ready to eat.
Keep in the refrigerator.

title: chicken and rice a la pastor
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour in all ingredients; mix thoroughly. After mixing, save 1/2 cup of the mix blend.
Pour ingredients into an ungreased baking pan (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch). Arrange chicken breasts on blended mixture.
Pour the reserved 1/2 cup of blended mixture over chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for an additional 15 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: chopped chicken livers
directions: Blend together thoroughly.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before serving. Spread on crackers.

title: harvest vegetable scallop
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine carrots, broccoli and 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Tuck potato slices into vegetable mixture at an angle.
Dot evenly with cheese spread.
Pour milk over vegetables; sprinkle with seasonings as desired.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate.
You can experiment with different fruits to your own taste.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets until skin comes off.
Strain juice and save some for canning.
Put sugar, vinegar, strained beet water and salt in container.
Let come to a boil.
Add cooked beets and cook 10 minutes.
Can with beets in liquid.

title: seven minute chicken dish
directions: Combine soups, water and chicken in large pan.
Add rice and stir to mix; bring quickly to boil.
Cover and reduce heat to medium low.
Simmer for 7 minutes.
Stir well and sprinkle onion rings on top.
Onion rings can be preheated in oven.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute
the
onions, pepper, celery and tomatoes in oleo for
2 hours.
Add garlic, let cook for about 10 minutes.	Add remaining ingredients, cook uncovered until done.
Cover, let sit
for 15 minutes.
(To make the etouffee go further, add an extra can of mushroom soup.)

title: vegetable bars
directions: Unroll rolls and bake on a cookie sheet.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and powder.
Spread on pastry.
Sprinkle with vegetables and cheese.
Press into spread.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: luscious lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown ground beef with onion, green pepper, mushrooms and salt to taste.
Drain; add tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Heat to thoroughly mix. Place 4 cooked noodles in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Layer half of ground beef mixture, all cottage cheese and 1 package Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with remaining 4 noodles and rest of meat mixture.
Top with packages of Mozzarella and Cheddar cheeses.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let set at least 15 minutes before serving.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time with a dash of salt in last egg. Add flour alternately with milk. Add vanilla. Mix well. Put in four cake pans lined with wax paper. Bake at 350° until done. Cool about ten minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix ingredients with fork until light pink. Chill 3 hours and serve.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: banana split pie
directions: Beat margarine with powdered sugar and eggs for 15 minutes. Pour mixture over pie crust.
Slice bananas over this.
Top with pineapple and whipped topping.
Dot with cherries; sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in a loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: white chocolate cookies
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Melt chocolate in oven.
When melted, pour over the cereal and mix together.
Drop from spoon and cool in refrigerator.

title: sharon's microwave pork chops and fried rice
directions: Use 1-quart glass bowl to heat the water, covered, in microwave until boiling, about 4 minutes. Stir in rice. Set aside. Micro-cook bacon 1 1/2 minutes until crisp and crumbly; set aside. Reserve 1 tablespoon drippings.
In a glass bowl, combine eggs and 2 tablespoons water and micro-cook 1 1/2 minutes. Cut into narrow strips.
In reserved drippings, stir in rice, bacon, eggs, onions and 3 tablespoons soy sauce. Arrange chops atop rice mixture in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch non-metal baking dish.
Micro-cook, covered, 5 minutes on High. Turn chops; micro-cook until done, about 6 minutes.

title: mashed potato supreme
directions: Peel potatoes, cut on and boil until done.
Drain potatoes and add all other ingredients, except for the Cheddar cheese.
Mix (whip) potatoes with electric mixer.

title: chocolate grasshopper cookies
directions: Prepare dough for Basic Sliced Cookies as directed, except reduce flour to 2 1/2 cups and mix in cocoa powder with the sugar. Shape and chill as directed.

title: vichyssiose(serves 4)
directions: Saute leeks and onions in butter until transparent.
Add potatoes, carrots, chicken broth, salt and pepper. Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer until veggies are tender.
Mash or process in food blender. Strain.
Return to heat and add the milk. Stir and blend well. Add seasoning and cool.
Add cream and chill several hours or overnight.
Serve in chilled soup bowls.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Use 2 boxes (3 ounce) lime jello as directed on package.
Let set.

title: french toast
directions: Combine eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, orange juice and orange rind. Beat until just blended.
Dip each slice of bread in egg mixture. Arrange on well buttered pan.
Combine cinnamon and 2 tablespoons of sugar and sprinkle over each slice.
Bake 10 minutes at 500° or until golden.

title: best in the west barbecue sauce
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, heat oil; add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally until veggies are tender.
Stir in ketchup, chili sauce, brown sugar, soy sauce, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and ground red pepper; increase heat to high.
Bring to a boil, reduce to low heat.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes until flavors are blended, uncovering to stir occasionally.
Remove from heat, cool.
Ladle into 1 pint jars, refrigerate, tightly covered, up to 2 weeks.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together.
Spread out on plate, then add on the toppings; lettuce (shredded), tomatoes (diced), cheese (shredded), olives, etc.
Anything to your taste.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach to package directions.
Drain.
Stir in mushroom soup and cheese.
Season to taste.
Cook until cheese is melted through.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, soup mix, water and stuffing mix and blend.
Bake in microwave 10 minutes.
Cover with wax paper. Drain grease off meat.
Combine catsup, brown sugar and dry mustard.
Spoon over meat loaf.
Cook in microwave 3 to 4 minutes until it is done in the middle.

title: six vegetable salad
directions: Drain beans, peas and corn; add pimento, pepper, onion and celery.
Mix well together.
Boil 5 minutes the remaining ingredients.
Cool mixture for 5 minutes and pour over vegetables. Refrigerate overnight.

title: buckeye candy balls
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and peanut butter together.
Form into buckeye-size balls.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
The next morning, melt paraffin wax; then add chocolate chips.
Put a toothpick in each peanut butter ball and swirl in chocolate, leaving a small portion uncoated to resemble a buckeye.
Makes 75 buckeyes.
Use leftover chocolate to cover pretzels or strawberries or the ends of cookies.
Enjoy.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs; add milk and mix well.
Stir in the dry ingredients, then the creamed corn. Stir in the melted butter.
Pour into greased baking dish. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in a 325° oven until firm for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: remolachas de argentina(beets)
directions: Cook and peel about 2 pounds beets.
Grate fine.
Heat butter in skillet; add grated beets and cook about 5 minutes.
Add cream, sugar and vinegar.
Heat gently and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put first five (going across) in a bowl, blend well.
Beat in powdered sugar, making a very stiff mixture.
Turn out on board and knead well.
Gradually work in nuts.
Put in a pan and chill or form in rolls.
Chill, then slice.

title: pat's skillet sausage
directions: In 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, cook sausage, breaking it into small pieces, with onion and green pepper, until sausage is browned.
Spoon off all fat.
Stir in tomatoes with their liquid, macaroni, sugar, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer, stirring often, about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in sour cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain off grease. Combine other ingredients. Add to ground beef and onions. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: kielbasa or smoked sausage
directions: Dissolve jello and catsup together.
Cut sausage in bite size pieces and place in slow cooker.
Pour jelly and catsup mixture over meat and let it simmer on low for 2 hours.
You can also put this in a heavy skillet on low heat and cook mixture for a lesser time.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter; stir in sliced onions and cook, covered, over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes.
Add salt and sugar, stir and cook another 15 minutes until onions are golden brown. Sprinkle flour over onions and stir.
Add bouillon which has been dissolved in 1 cup boiling water.
Add garlic, bay leaf and a little pepper.
Add 4 (or more) cups water and cook (simmer) for 20 minutes.
Put into bowls, place a slice of bread (which has been dried in the oven) on top and put a slice of cheese on top. Heat in oven at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: city club cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Blend in egg and vanilla, adding flour, soda and salt.
Add chopped pecans.
Chill and shape into balls the size of a quarter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Press with the bottom of a glass to flatten.
Bake 10-12
minutes at 350 degrees.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box; drain.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, mix the macaroni, soup, Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Pour macaroni mixture into baking pan.
Pour milk over macaroni, then slice remaining butter and place on top.
Sprinkle with pepper; top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: sauerbraten
directions: For marinade, in large bowl, combine vinegar, water, wine, 3 of the sliced onions, brown sugar, bay leaves, 2 teaspoons cloves, 2 teaspoons salt, 1 teaspoon mustard seed and 1/2 teaspoon peppercorns.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and butter together and spread in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and Cool Whip together and put on top of pretzels.
Mix jello, strawberries and boiling water and put on top of whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry tea punch
directions: Mix water and tea in large container.
Puree strawberries, lemonade and sugar with crushed ice in blender.
Mix pureed liquids with tea mixture; stir thoroughly.
Serve in punch bowl with ice ring and sliced oranges.

title: cream cheese stuffed chicken
directions: Cut cream cheese into 4 sticks.
Pound chicken to about 1/3 to 1/2-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place cheese in center of each piece.
Roll up.
Coat with flour; dip into mixture of egg and water.
Coat with crumb and parsley mixture. Cover; chill for 1 hour.
Fry in oil heated to medium high in wok or deep skillet.
Cook until browned, turning carefully if necessary.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves 4.

title: mild salsa
directions: Cook to boiling; add 2 tablespoons cornstarch with 1/4 cup cold water.
Cook, stirring, until clear and a bit thickened.
I do this recipe 4 times to make a batch to can, usually 5 pints. Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: dip for salads
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill.
Serve with carrots, broccoli or cauliflower.
Makes 1 pint.

title: chili
directions: Pour stewed tomatoes into a bowl and mash with a potato masher if large chunks of tomato in the chili are undesirable.
Add all ingredients to the ground beef.
Additional brown sugar, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce can be added depending on one's taste.
Simmer for 30 minutes or several hours in a crock-pot on low heat.

title: holiday salad
directions: Take the liquid from the pineapple and oranges to get 3 1/2 cups of liquid for the jello.
If not enough, add water to make it. Dissolve the jello; let cool.
Then add the other ingredients and pour in mold or a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Clean and coarsely chop vegetables.
Place all ingredients, except cream, in a 2-quart saucepan, adding a little more stock or water, if needed to cook vegetables.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, 30 to 45 minutes. Ladle the contents of the pan into a blender and puree (completely).
Keep one hand on lid of blender so hot liquid does not spray you.
Add cream and reheat to serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Peel and grind zucchini to pulp.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Grease 3 cake pans.
Cream sugar, margarine and shortening together.
Sift soda and flour together; add alternately with milk and egg yolks, added one at a time, beating well.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks.
Fold into batter; then add pecans and coconut. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix together, spread on hamburger buns.
Wrap in foil and put in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix meat, rice, onions and seasonings.
Shape into balls and brown, turning frequently.
Add sauce and water.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add water, if necessary.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute in margarine onion, celery and pepper.
Mix together soup, sour cream, cheese, corn and beans.
Add onion mixture to this and add salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Put in 2-quart greased casserole dish.
On top of mixture, add 1 row Ritz crackers, mashed and mixed with 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: In a buttered 8-inch square pan, pour in fruit, spreading evenly.
Mix flour, sugar, oatmeal, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and egg until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of fruit and nuts; drizzle oleo over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked red snapper
directions: Melt butter or margarine in the bottom of a baking dish. Place red snapper in a single layer and then cover with white sauce.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes; check doneness with a fork.
Don't overcook.
Serve with rice, the sauce makes a great gravy.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes until tender and drain.
Mash until smooth, adding remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook the first three ingredients for 20 minutes.
Add carrots, potatoes and mixed vegetables and cook for 30 minutes.
Add the 2 cans of soup and the cheese.
Stir well until all the cheese is melted.

title: apple-carrot cake
directions: Combine mix, oil and eggs.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Add applesauce and beat 1 minute.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Brown butter and flour in skillet.
Add juice from asparagus, cheese and bread crumbs; mix well.
Add milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Add asparagus, mixing well.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with sliced, boiled eggs.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix; roll and cut.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then gradually add the remainder of ingredients to mixture.
Add milk last.
Depending on consistency of mixture you might need to add a little more milk, not too much. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each egg is added.
Blend in all the flour; beat well. Add lemon extract.

title: creole okra in tomatoes
directions: Slice enough okra to fill a large iron skillet.
Put meal on okra.
Melt enough butter in skillet to coat all of okra when stirred in.
Put in medium hot oven; cook until as brown as desired.
Stir occasionally.

title: hermits
directions: Mix together thoroughly shortening, brown sugar and eggs. Stir in coffee.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix into dough, raisins and chopped nuts.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake until set, just until, when touched lightly with finger, almost no imprint remains.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: turtle pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small heavy saucepan, low heat, melt caramels with 1/3 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Spread on bottom of pastry shell.
In medium pan, low heat, melt chocolate with butter.
In large bowl, beat eggs with remaining milk, water, vanilla and salt.
Add chocolate mixture; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Top with pecans.

title: sesame cookies
directions: Toast sesame seed 5 to 8 minutes in 375° oven until brown.

title: mrs. ruby's fried pies
directions: Sweeten apples to taste and let cool.
Mix dough and roll out into circles.
Fill half with apples, fold over and press edges together to close.
Fry in Crisco on both sides to golden brown. Makes about 25 pies.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Soak beans for 12 hours and drain.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Blend Oreo cookies and butter in blender or food processor. Pack into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Freeze.
Soften ice cream and spread over cookie base.
Drizzle caramel topping over ice cream. Freeze. Spread Cool Whip over frozen ice cream and top with nuts and cherries.

title: texas hash(microwave)
directions: Combine meat, onions, peppers and garlic.
Microwave on High 5 minutes. Stir several times. Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings. Cook on High 12 to 15 minutes.
If more liquid is desired, add 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat
eggs.
Add
margarine,
syrup,
vanilla, oatmeal, salt and
sugar with flour.
Combine all ingredients and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes. Good if you add nuts or raisins (1 cup).

title: beef and potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Spread in 2-quart baking dish or pan. Cover with potatoes, onion soup mix and salt.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover and top with grated cheese; bake, uncovered, for about 15 minutes longer.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix water and oats; let stand 20 minutes.
Cream together shortening, brown sugar, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients; add oats.
Blend well.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: skinny soup
directions: Brown turkey in large pan; add tomato juice.
Chop all vegetables and mix in with juice and turkey.
Simmer 3 hours.

title: arja's sweet potato christmas casserole(finnish)
directions: Boil potatoes in water with skins on.
Peel while hot and mash until fine.
Add flour and mix.
Let sit in warm place for a minimum of 2 hours (mixture becomes sweet).
Add milk, butter and salt.
Pour mixture into a large buttered casserole dish or 2 medium ones.
Leave room to rise.
Bake at 275° for 2 to 3 hours. Serve warm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: jam pie
directions: Blend together. Put in an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and ginger together.
Cream shortening until smooth.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and molasses.
Add flour alternately with milk. Beat until smooth.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake for 12 minutes at 400°.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: cinnamon carrot muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix baking powder, cinnamon, salt and oat bran in large bowl.
Mix with milk, a little at a time, then stir in carrots, raisins, sugar, oil, egg and flour.
Spoon batter into muffin pan which has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Add milk, salad oil and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Add topping.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour dry cake mix over top.
Pour melted butter over top of cake.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: acini de pepe fruit salad
directions: Drain and save juices from pineapple, oranges and fruit cocktail.
Refrigerate drained fruit.
Mix juices with sugar, flour and eggs; cook until thick.
Cook macaroni according to directions; rinse and drain.
Pour juices which you prepared over macaroni and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add fruit and Cool Whip.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Cream the cheese.
Add juice from can of clams or crabs.
Mix until creamy.
Add horseradish to your taste, then add milk and salt and top with the pepper.
Great dip with chips.

title: slaw
directions: Mix together vinegar, sugar, and water.
Heat this mixture and let it get cold, then mix with cabbage, etc.
Keep in refrigerator. Wait 24 hours before serving.
Keeps several days.

title: hazel's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger with salt and pepper.
Add garlic, basil, tomato paste, mushrooms, olives and spaghetti sauce.
Mix in a separate bowl cottage cheese, egg, Parmesan cheese, pepper and parsley.
Boil lasagna noodles.
Layer in a greased pan, noodles, then meat sauce, then cottage cheese mix and then grated cheese. Repeat.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: barbecue-style meat loaf
directions: Crumble dry bread to fine consistency.
Combine ground beef, onion, bread, egg, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Mix well and shape into loaf.
Place in appropriate size baking dish.

title: oven "fried" chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into approximately 1-inch slices.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Melt margarine in small bowl.
Spread crackers on waxed paper; crush crackers finely with rolling pin. Dip seasoned chicken in margarine then roll in cracker crumbs, coating well.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet close together. Pour any excess margarine over pieces.
Sprinkle excess crumbs over pieces.
Bake in a 350° oven approximately 40 to 45 minutes, until crumbs begin to brown.

title: white salad
directions: Mash together pineapple and cream cheese.
Make jello using water and pineapple juice.
Set jello in refrigerator until mushy. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in long container and chill until set. Cut into squares to serve.

title: sicillian meat roll
directions: In bowl, combine eggs and tomato juice.
Stir in the bread crumbs, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Add ground beef.
Mix well.
On waxed paper or foil pat meat into a 10 x 8-inch rectangle pan.
Arrange ham slices atop meat, leaving small margin around edges.
Reserve 1 slice cheese.
Tear up remaining cheese.
Sprinkle over ham.
Starting from short end, carefully roll up meat using paper or foil to lift.
Seal edges and ends. Place roll seamside down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/4 hours.
Cut reserved cheese slice in 4 triangles.
Lay atop meat.
Return to oven until cheese melts (about 2 minutes).

title: steve's dish
directions: Brown meat, drain.
Put back in skillet, add diced onion and bell pepper and saute.
Add cooked rice.
Serve with Ranch Style beans.

title: easy day frosting
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan; add cocoa and milk.
Bring mixture to a boil; remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla and pecans (if desired).
Beat by hand until well blended.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions, green peppers and salt and let stand for 3 hours.
Bring to a boil vinegar-water combination, sugar, turmeric, mustard seed and cloves.
Add pickles and heat through. Stir and boil a few minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.
Makes 9 pints.

title: peggy's fruit salad
directions: In colander, drain the pineapple, mandarin oranges and cherries.
Add the apple and dump into a large bowl. Mix.
(The juice from the fruit helps keep the apple from turning dark.)
Add the other ingredients and toss gently to mix.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Use 9 x 13 pan.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water; set aside.
Mix cottage cheese, crushed pineapple, celery, nuts and lemon juice with Jell-O.
Let congeal in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Take two parts unselfishness and one part of patience and work together.
Add plenty of industry, lighten with good spirits and sweeten with kindness.
Put in smiles as thick as raisins in plum pudding and bake by warmth which steams from a loving heart.
If this fails to make a good day, the fault is not with the recipe but with the cook.

title: chicken pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir good.
Then add the other ingredients.
Put in pie shell and put the other crust on top.
Cook in 350° or 375° oven until golden brown.

title: southern burgers
directions: Brown beef and onion in a little hot fat in skillet.
Stir in catsup, mustard and soup.
Simmer until mixture has thickened a little, about 15 minutes.
Spoon over toasted split buns or English muffin halves.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Brown both the hamburger and the sausage, then drain.
Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot and cook on high for 2 hours.

title: carrot bread
directions: Simmer first 9 ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Blend sugar and cornstarch in a 2
or 3 qt. pan.
Add milk and eggs and mix thoroughly.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens, stirring frequently.
Remove pan from heat.
Add vanilla to taste and blend well.
Pour into the freezer can of ice cream maker.
Add condensed and evaporated milk and mix well. Refrigerate until cool.
Begin the freezing process following the directions for the ice cream maker.
Makes one gallon.

title: green stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill until ready to serve.

title: citrus salad in orange cups
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat; cover and chill 1 hour.
Cut a 1/2-inch slice from the stem end of each orange, clip membrane and carefully remove pulp.
(Do not puncture rind.)
Drain orange cups on paper towels.
Remove membrane from orange pulp, cut pulp into bite size pieces. Combine orange pieces, grapefruit sections and strawberries; drain.
Spoon fruit mixture evenly into orange cups; set aside. Beat whipping cream until stiff peaks form.
Fold into chilled honey mixture.
Spoon mixture over orange cups.
Yields 6 servings.

title: baked salmon
directions: Rub the salmon inside and out with salt and pepper; dredge with flour.
Put into a well-greased narrow baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes, then add the butter, onion, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and tomatoes.
Reduce heat to 375°. Bake for 30 minutes longer, basting frequently.

title: new orleans red beans
directions: Bring water to boil in large pot with beans.
Add all ingredients.
Boil for 1/2 hour.
Reduce heat to simmer; continue to cook for 3 hours, or until tender.
Any other dry beans may be used for this recipe.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix cake by hand. Pat out in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cream the last 3 ingredients. Pour over mixture in pan. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: wiener stew
directions: Saute onions and peppers in a large frying pan.
Add soup and 2 cans of water.
Bring to boil and then simmer.
Add salt and pepper.
Add flour and water to thicken mix.
Split hot dogs lengthwise and cut in half.
Add to tomato mix and continue cooking for a short time.
Boil potatoes and mash.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets with Crisco.
Combine Crisco, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat on medium speed until well blended.
Add oats, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon to the creamed mixture.
Beat at low speed just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: crab appetizers
directions: Allow butter or margarine and cheese to come to room temperature.
Blend cheese and butter together with a mixer.
With the tines of a fork, shred the crabmeat and chop finely.
Add the chopped onion and the shredded crabmeat and blend.
Spread on the cocktail rye and broil in the broiler until the top is lightly browned.
Makes approximately 30.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Heat milk and add sugar, salt, butter and honey; stir until butter melts, then cool.
Dissolve yeast in water and stir into milk mixture.
Add white flour and 2 1/2 cups whole wheat flour. Beat until smooth; add remaining flour.
Knead; let rise to double (approximately 1 1/4 hours).
Punch down.
Shape into loaves and brush with melted butter.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes two large loaves.

title: scratch brownies
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Add sugar, then other ingredients.
Microwave on High 5 1/2 to 6 minutes.

title: magic muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until flour is moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 400°. Makes 12 muffins.

title: happy day cake
directions: Measure dry ingredients together.
Beat shortening to soften, mix sugar, next beat one egg at a time until fluffy.
Mix milk and other dry ingredients a little at a time until the texture is nice and smooth.
Beat on medium speed for about 2 minutes after all ingredients are mixed.
Bake in a 375° oven about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare and core apples and thinly slice apples to make 6 cups. If apples lack tartness, sprinkle with teaspoon of lemon juice.

title: hamburger mushroom casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions.
Drain well.
Add softened cheese, soup, milk and ketchup.
Mix.
Add olives and salt.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes in a lightly greased shallow 8 to 10-inch square casserole dish.
Place biscuits on top and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 6 hours.

title: creamy-sure fudge
directions: Use a heavy saucepan and stir constantly to avoid scorching the sugar, milk, butter, Marshmallow Creme or marshmallows and salt in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture has boiled exactly 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate pieces and vanilla and stir until chocolate has melted.
Stir in walnuts. Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Let stand until firm, then cut into squares.

title: 24 hour egg omelet
directions: Trim crust from bread, butter slices or bread and place in a greased pan or baking dish.
Cover entire bottom with bread.

title: broccoli cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower according to package directions. Mix together soup, sour cream and cheese.
Arrange cooked vegetables in a shallow casserole.
Pour sauce over them.
Put crushed corn flakes on top.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix dressing, soup mix and cranberry sauce.
Place chicken and sauce mixture in greased baking dish and bake at 350 for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Serve with rice.

title: oyster stuffing(folks will "gobble" this up!)
directions: Bake in oven at 400° or in turkey!

title: pork chops dijon
directions: You will need an outdoor barbecue or grill.

title: baked red snapper
directions: Spray Pam on bottom of baking dish.
Season fish to taste. Slice onion and bell pepper and place over fish.
Add cream of mushroom soup on top of fish evenly.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable soup stock
directions: Chop all veggies and put in a big pan. Boil for 1 hour.
This is easy to can in quart jars or freeze in quart bags.

title: orange cake
directions: Grate the rind of orange.
Take the juice and put in a cup and fill with water.
Heat this to boiling hot.
Then sift flour and baking powder.

title: poppy seed fruit salad dressing
directions: Combine sugar, salt and dry mustard.
Stir in vinegar.
Beat at medium speed.
Gradually add oil and beat until thick.
Add poppy seed.
Especially good with watermelon, blueberries, cantaloupe, peaches, bananas and apples.

title: frozen pineapple pie
directions: Beat cream cheese at room temperature.
Blend in sugar and egg yolks well.
Add pineapple and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites and whipped cream.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze overnight.
May be stored for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Combine the margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat 2 or 3 minutes.
Stir in buttermilk and bananas.
Add flour mixture and stir only until everything is combined.
Add pecans, if desired.
Fill 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chile beans
directions: Cook beef, onions and garlic until beef is done; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 35 or 40 minutes.

title: rice chex tarts
directions: Mix together Rice Chex, flour and salt.
Cream margarine and cream cheese and add to Rice Chex mixture.
Work with hands until mixture holds together.
Press into tart pans.
Press out and up sides.
Do not grease pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden.
Remove to cool.
Fill with ham, chicken or egg salad.

title: heavenly cookies
directions: Cream mixture until light and fluffy.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Optional:
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers and onions. Cover with cold brine (1/4 cup salt to each quart of water).
Drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mace, cayenne, mustard seed and turmeric.
Boil 3 minutes. Add drained cucumbers and onions. Bring mixture to boiling point.
Pack in hot jars; seal at once.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: avocado and tomato bake
directions: Cut tomatoes in half horizontally, then scoop out and reserve the pulp.
Take care not to pierce skins.
Place tomato shells in greased microwave dish.
Cut avocado in half lengthwise and twist the 2 halves apart; pry out seed.
Grip skin at the pointed ends and peel back to remove.
Cut flesh into 1/2-inch cubes and put in large bowl.
Sprinkle the lemon juice over avocado, then add reserved tomato pulp and basil.
Season to taste with Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Then carefully stir in 1/2 shredded cheese.
Place avocado mixture into tomato shells, dividing it equally and pile it up neatly.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cook on Medium-high until hot and cheese melts. Garnish with basil sprigs and serve.

title: swedish tea bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water for 5 minutes.
Then add lukewarm milk and about half of the flour to make a soft batter. Beat well.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double.
Add sugar, salt, melted butter, raisins, pecans, dates, cherries and remaining flour.
Place dough in bowl and let rise until double. Shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, reduce heat to 325° and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes 30 minutes or until tender; drain. Beat potatoes and butter at medium speed until smooth. Add eggs and next 6 ingredients, beating well. Pour evenly into pie crusts and bake at 350° on lower oven rack for 45 to 50 minutes or until set. Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: steak -n- rice
directions: Brown meat after rolling in flour.
Add green pepper and onion and brown.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.
One cup rice to 3 cups water.

title: 1 cup salad
directions: Mix together and serve well chilled.

title: minestrone soup(italian)
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in oil until soft.
Add tomatoes, bouillon cubes, 1 1/2 quarts of water, celery and cabbage.
Bring to a boil and simmer about 30 minutes until vegetables are tender. Add seasonings, beans and shells.
Simmer 5 to 10 more minutes. Stir in grated cheese and serve. Serves 4 to 6.
Preparation time: 10 to 20 minutes.
Cooking time:
40 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch dish.
Slice cookie dough into slices and form a crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese and mix with Cool Whip.
Spread on top of crust.
Arrange fresh fruit on top of spread.

title: pecan pie
directions: Boil sugar and syrup about 2 minutes.
Pour slowly over beaten eggs, stirring vigorously.
Add margarine, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: nighty night cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees when you begin to prepare recipe.

title: swiss chicken quiche(or pie if you don't eat quiche)
directions: Put chicken in bottom of pie shell.
Lay cheese slices on top of chicken.
Beat together remaining ingredients and pour over chicken and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Put warm water in bowl with yeast and let dissolve. Add sugar and salt. Stir in enough flour to make a smooth dough. Turn out the dough on lightly floured surface and use excess flour to knead into dough. Knead until smooth.

Divide into 18 to 24 pieces; roll into balls. Roll each ball into a long strip (snake). Curve each strip into a horse shoe shape. Lift up the ends and twist them once around each other. Fold over the ends and rest them on top of the curve, forming a pretzel shape. Brush pretzels with a mixture of egg beaten with a little water. Sprinkle pretzel with coarse salt. Bake on greased pan at 425° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vegetable-cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Melt cheese and soup in onion.
Add vegetables, rice and chicken, if desired.
Bake in a 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pineapple banana tube cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, soda, salt, sugar and cinnamon together.
Add bananas to flour mixture.
Add oil, vanilla, eggs, pineapple and juice.
Stir mixture gently until well mixed.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool completely in pan before removing.

title: easy dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together with packages of taco seasoning.
Spread thin on 2 cookie sheets.
Fry hamburger with salt, pepper and onion.
Let cool.
Sprinkle on the dip.
Grate cheese and sprinkle on top of hamburger.
Add your optionals. Dip taco chips in.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Add salt to sliced tomatoes and onions.
Cover with ice water; let stand 1 hour.
In large pot, combine vinegar, sugar, celery and mustard seed.
Bring to boil.
Drain tomatoes and onions; rinse.
Add to vinegar; let simmer.
Do not boil.
Pack in hot, sterile jars and seal.
Makes about 5 pints.
You can add a little hot pepper if you would like to spice them up.

title: fudge
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl except nuts.
Microwave on (50% power) Medium until chocolate is melted, 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in nuts; pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Refrigerate. Makes 2 pounds.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion and garlic, then add meat.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Add mushrooms and cook 6 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in consomme, vinegar and tomato paste. Simmer 10 minutes.
Blend in sour cream just before serving.

title: low-fat banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; grease and flour only the bottoms and 1/2-inch up sides of two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Cream sugar and Butter Buds.
Add eggs, sour cream (or yogurt) and bananas; mix until blended.
Stir flour to moisten.
Fold in nuts and pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, remove to rack. Wrap tightly and store in refrigerator.

title: jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: cheese and eggs ole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in bottom of casserole dish.
Combine all other ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes or until done.
Serve immediately. Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Serve with salsa, guacamole and sour cream and a huge basket of crispy tortilla chips.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add frozen berries and stir until dissolved.
Add applesauce.
Refrigerate until firm.
Top with marshmallows and sour cream.

title: ranch salad(for 16 to 20 servings)
directions: Combine vegetables, bacon and cheese in large salad bowl. Combine salad dressings and pour over salad.
Toss to mix.
Chill. Yields 16 to 20 servings.

title: pickled beans and corn
directions: Break beans and cook until done.
Pour water from beans.
Boil corn on cob.
Cool and cut from cob.
Mix together and place in large jar.
Mix remaining ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Pour over the beans and corn already in jar.
Place weights over mixture and cover tightly for 9 days.
After this, you may can or leave in jar.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat at high speed (approximately 2 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: my grandmother's chicken croquettes
directions: Put the onion and lemon rind into 1 quart of milk; let it come almost to a boil.
Break into a bowl the eggs, minus the yolk of one.
Add parsley, nutmeg and red pepper.
Into a large saucepan, but butter, cornstarch and flour; cream these.
As soon as milk comes nearly to a boil, remove onion and lemon rind.
Pour over creamed butter and flour, stirring all the time.
Add eggs, parsley and seasoning; when thickened, add the meat.
Taste for seasoning; pour on flat dish to cool.
Mold into croquettes, using large, pointed wine glass.
Dip into yolk of egg which was put aside.
Mix with 3 tablespoons of milk; roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in deep hot lard.
Serves 10.

title: stuffed red peppers(our favorite)
directions: Place beef, onion, celery and garlic in a bowl.
Stir in rice, egg, half of tomato sauce, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Fill red peppers with beef mixture, mounding the tops. Arrange peppers in a line, standing upright.
Cover with remaining tomato sauce.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl, mixing well.
Pour into greased pan. Bake for 45 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: souper tuna noodle bake
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender, stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until hot, stir.
Top with sliced cheese and croutons if desired.
Bake until cheese melts.
Makes about 5 1/2 cups.

title: gladys' banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas; add oil and eggs and beat.
Add other ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans; pour in batter and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done in middle.

title: honey chicken
directions: Mix salt, honey, mustard and margarine together.
Place chicken in a baking pan skin side up.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cover with foil if chicken gets too brown.

title: famous fudge sauce
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add 1/4 cup water and make smooth paste.
Add remaining 1/4 cup water and stir over heat until it boils for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla when off heat. This sauce thickens when it cools.

title: magic wands
directions: Line baking sheets with waxed paper.
Melt semi-sweet chocolate in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling water.
Remove from heat; dip pretzel rods into chocolate to coat about 3/4 of pretzels.
Place on prepared baking sheet.
Refrigerate until chocolate is firm.
Melt white chocolate in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling, water.
Stir in food colors to make orange. Remove from heat; dip coated pretzels into colored chocolate to coat about 1/4 of the pretzel.
Place on baking sheet; immediately top with sprinkles.
Refrigerate until chocolate is firm.
Tie ends with ribbons to resemble magic wands.
Great for halloween.

title: pennsylvania dutch pastry
directions: Cut together salt, flour and shortening.
Beat water and egg together, add vinegar.
Add to flour mixture.
Makes pastry for two crust pie plus one single crust.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and oleo together.
Put in bottom of pan.
Fix Dream Whip, add sugar and cream cheese; mix well.
Pour half over graham cracker crumbs, put cherry pie filling over that. Then cover with rest of Dream Whip mixture.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top.
Put in refrigerator to set, about 1 hour or overnight.

title: prize winning sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and rest of ingredients.

title: tabasco beef ring
directions: Mix your favorite meat loaf, then pat out flat on counter top. Top with Mozzarella cheese and mushrooms.
Roll up.
Make sure all sides are sealed or the cheese will run out all over the pan when baking.
Bake as directed.
Pour spaghetti sauce over top and bake the last 15 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs(svenska kottbullar)
directions: Mix bread crumbs, milk and thick cream and let the mixture soak for approximately 10 minutes.
Mix ground meat with salt, white or black pepper and onion.
Add the bread crumb mixture. Stir until smooth but not too much or the fat will creep out and the mixture will become dry.
Form into small meatballs of uniform size.
Fry them in a little butter in a frying pan.
Lower the heat when the balls are well browned so that they have time to get thoroughly cooked.
Shake the pan now and then while frying so that the meatballs become round and evenly colored.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Grease a large casserole or 9-inch pan.
Mix together well hash brown potatoes, potato soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and garlic powder.
Pour into casserole; sprinkle over top corn flakes and oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be doubled.

title: ruth smith's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and oil.
Add eggs and blend.
Add baking powder, salt, vanilla and lemon flavorings, pudding mix and milk. Blend these ingredients and gradually add flour.
Mixture will appear stiff, this is okay.
Grease and flour tube pan before pouring in mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 90 minutes.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper in oil.
Add meat and brown. Drain well.
Add tomato paste, water, dry mustard, sugar and garlic.
Season to taste.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.
The longer it simmers, the better it is.
Boil spaghetti and serve with meat sauce.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as usual.
Cool.
Break into bite size pieces.
Make 1 layer of cake, then spread pudding over it, then put 1 can (drained) pineapple, then put 1 can cherries.
Slice 1/2 of the bananas on top of the cherries.
Mix nuts and Cool Whip together. Spread on top.
Then repeat cake and etc. again topping with Cool Whip.
Make 1 punch bowl full.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Cook slowly until 1/3 teaspoon forms a hard ball when dropped in water.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Combine syrup mixture with egg whites.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and allow to harden before serving.

title: tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, cream butter or margarine and 1/2 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add water and vanilla.
Gradually add flour and nuts, beating until well mixed.
Chill for 30 minutes or until firm.
Roll dough into one inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown on bottom. Cool 10 minutes and roll in 1 cup confectioners sugar.
When completely cool, roll again in remaining confectioners sugar. Yields 4 dozen cookies, about 80 calories each.

title: banana chiffon
directions: Beat 5 egg whites stiff with cream of tartar (reserve 2 egg whites for frosting).
Mix first 4 ingredients.
Make a well and add remaining 5 ingredients; mix by hand.
Fold yellow mixture into egg whites.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts (optional).
Bake in angel food tube pan at 350° for 55 minutes.
Turn pan upside down to cool.

title: aleta jones' applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and applesauce; sift cinnamon, flour and baking soda.
Combine.
Add raisins last, coated with a little of the flour.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Use a greased and floured pan.

title: italian bowtie bake
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package; drain.
In a bowl combine the spaghetti sauce and salad dressing mix; add pasta and toss to coat.
Transfer to a greased shallow 2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 4 servings.

title: bud's cole slaw
directions: Requires two bowls:
one large and one medium size.
In medium size bowl, mix up all ingredients except cabbage, carrots and onion.
In large bowl, put cabbage, carrots and onion; toss to mix. Cover with contents of medium bowl and mix again.
Chill for 4 hours before serving.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Pour melted butter over pecans, dates, coconut and candy slices and let stand.
Beat eggs, sugar, flour with soda sifted in, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for about 2 hours.

title: greek hamburg
directions: Mix and simmer for 35 minutes.

title: disappearing chile
directions: Brown meat and pepper; drain.
Add beans, tomatoes and seasoning mix.
Heat until bubbly.
Separate dough.
Place cheese cube in each and fold over; seal well.
Roll in butter; coat with crumbs.
Arrange biscuits on top of mixture.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 22 minutes until brown.
Cook in 2-quart casserole.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix in a large bowl the frozen hash browns, melted butter, onions, sour cream, mushroom soup and half of the Cheddar cheese. Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Top with remaining cheese. Take bag of chips and crumble into small pieces. Cover entire dish with chips. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes, then decrease to 350 degrees and bake for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: butter rolls
directions: Make biscuit dough.
Cut out dough the size of a saucer.
Put 1 slice of butter, 1 tablespoon sugar and 2 drops of vanilla on dough.
Roll 1/2 dough over the other half.
Press edges down with fork.
Place in pan and cook at 350° in oven until dough is done.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion, zucchini and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons of oil.
Set aside.
Coat chicken generously with McCormick seasoning and cut into bite-size pieces.
Brown chicken and add vegetables when chicken is done.
Add 1 teaspoon cornstarch to tomato juice and pour over chicken.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Arrange following ingredients in this order: chips, 2 cups rice, meat sauce, cheese, chopped onions, lettuce, tomatoes, black olives, picante sauce, coconut and pecans.

title: yorkshire dinner
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, celery and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Bake in casserole, uncovered.

title: garden pizza
directions: Spread rolls on ungreased pans (13 x 9-inch size).
Press seams together.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, until brown.
Set aside to cool.

title: wacky cake
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Add rest.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice; add other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: maui ginger salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend well and refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip pecan bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, oats and brown sugar.
Using 2 knives or pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Reserve 1/2 cup.
Press remaining mixture in bottom of greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes in 350°
oven.
Remove and cool for 15 minutes.
Pour condensed milk over cooled mixture. Spread evenly.
Cover with pecans and chips.
Top with reserved 1/2 cup crumb mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool before cutting.

title: chocolate mint cookies
directions: In large pan, cook butter, sugar and water until melted.
Add chocolate until partially melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir until chips melt.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes. With mixer on high, beat in eggs one at a time.
Reduce speed to low and add dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Chill dough 1 hour. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place them 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Place 1/2 mint on top.
When it starts to melt, swirl on cookie top.

title: buttermilk raisin scones
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside. Cream together sugar and butter until it is the texture of sand. Add alternately the flour and buttermilk.
Fold in raisins and orange zest.
Line a 9 inch cake pan with plastic wrap.
Put dough in and cover up.
Refrigerate until firm, or can be frozen at this point (wrap well).
Cut into 8 wedges.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet or a parchment lined cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Combine sour cream and egg.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken in sour cream mixture, then into crumb mixture.
Place in oiled pan and bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, stir first ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans. Pour into pie crust. Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Cool on wire rack. Makes 8 servings.

title: blackberry jelly
directions: Crush thoroughly the fully ripe berries.
Place in jelly bag and squeeze out juice.

title: sweet 'n sour kielbasa
directions: Add all ingredients into a crock-pot and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours.
You'll love it!
Serve with toothpicks.

title: mushroom caviar
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden brown.
Add mushrooms and saute for 5 minutes, stirring to mix well.
Add the lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and remove from stove.
Now add enough mayonnaise to blend and add the salt and pepper to taste.
Mound into an attractive ball on one of your favorite serving dishes, cover and place in the refrigerator until well chilled.
Serve with Melba toast or your favorite cracker.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend cottage cheese until smooth and creamy.
Add lemon juice and buttermilk and blend thoroughly.
Place in bowl.
Add crab meat, celery and frozen peas.
Mix thoroughly.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onions.
Place in alternate layers in buttered casserole, seasoning each layer and pouring over white sauce.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle cheese on the last 20 minutes of baking.

title: play-time dough
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In medium bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups flour, salt and cream of tartar; mix well. In small bowl, mix boiling water, oil and food coloring.
Add to flour mixture; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened. Cool to room temperature, about 3 minutes.
On lightly floured surface, knead in up to 1/4 cup flour until dough is smooth, about 3 minutes.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 1 1/2 cups of fun.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Coat beef with flour.
Heat skillet; add 2 tablespoons butter. Add meat and brown.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cook for 3 or 4 minutes or until onion is crisp and tender.
Remove meat, mushrooms and onion.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to skillet; blend in 3 tablespoons flour and tomato paste.
Slowly stir in beef stock or broth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick. Return meat; stir and cook until meat is tender.
Just before you serve, add sour cream.
Cook slowly until heated.
Do not boil! Serve over noodles.

title: beef-n-tortilla casserole
directions: Brown beef in a heavy skillet.
Add onions, green peppers and seasonings; saute about 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and soups. Cook an additional 5 minutes over low heat.
Line bottom of buttered 9 x 11-inch glass baking dish with 4 tortillas, torn in half.
Cover with 1/2 of meat mixture.
Cover with remaining tortillas, torn in half and cover with the other half of meat mixture.
Cover all with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk.
Add yeast mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Knead lightly; roll out.
Cut.
Put in greased pan. Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: american beauty cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and let stand.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and coloring; beat well.
Add buttermilk, salt, vanilla and flour.
Beat well, remove from mixer. Add vinegar and baking soda by hand.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 3 layers or in loaf pans for grooms cake.

title: lucille harper's fruit cake
directions: Grease pans with butter or margarine.
Line with brown paper and grease paper.
Preheat oven to 275°.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Dredge fruit in flour; add salt, nuts and coconut.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 275° oven.
Store in airtight container 5 days before serving.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Remove meat from bones.
Make gravy with broth.
Boil vegetables and noodles until soft.
Add everything together in loaf pan or casserole.
Mix Bisquick and drop with tablespoon on top.
Bake until frown.

title: 7 can soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onions.	Drain and combine with other ingredients in crock pot.
Cook on low setting for 4 hours. Serves 8-10.

title: pesto
directions: Place ingredients in a blender or food processor.
Whirl until basil is finely chopped and mixture is well blended.
Spoon over hot cooked food.
If made ahead, place in small jars and pour on a thin layer of olive oil to prevent darkening.
Refrigerate for up to 1 week; freeze for longer storage.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: zucchini
directions: Combine zucchini, tomato and onion; season with parsley. Simmer over low heat until zucchini is barely done.
Serves 4.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease or spray Pam in a Bundt pan. Set aside.
Beat and mix the Crisco and sugar until creamy and fluffy.
Add milk and sour cream, then add 1 egg at a time.
Mix in bananas.
Slowly add and mix in remaining dry ingredients. Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab meat quiche
directions: Mix together flour, Crisco and salt.
Add water slowly. Refrigerate dough 1/2 hour.
Roll out to make pie shells.
Makes 2 pie shells.

title: velvet pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add one egg at a time and beat.
Add vanilla and almond extract and beat.
Then add flour, one cup at a time, and gradually add milk until all 3 cups of flour are used.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300° or until it's firm.

title: brownie delight
directions: Make brownie mix as directed. Divide in half. Mix pudding as directed. Divide in half. In a large bowl, layer half of brownies, then half of pudding, then half of Cool Whip and half of crushed candy bars. Repeat layers, topping with candy.

title: grandma's beer bread(especially good just out of the oven!)
directions: Mix together.
Place in greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together well.
Place in small serving bowl and top with chopped nuts, if desired.
Or, place cheese on a piece of plastic wrap or wax paper and shape in ball.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Form into ball and roll in chopped pecans or walnuts.
Yields 2 medium balls.

title: handy pastry
directions: Mix all well.
Handle as little as possible.
May be stored two weeks in refrigerator.

title: sweet & sour
directions: Fry sausage. Add all other ingredients. Cook until mixed well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Use 9 x 13 casserole. Mix all ingredients. Pour into casserole pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, butter, eggs and syrup; beat
until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan; bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool completely in pan.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Place
sliced potatoes into flat casserole dish.
Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo until done.
Add mushrooms, soup and Ro-Tel;
heat
and stir until blended.
Add cubed Velveeta and pour
mixture
over
potatoes.
Bake
at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until flavors blend.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: venison tenderloin
directions: In cast-iron pan, cook bacon until crisp.
Put cooked bacon in oven at 200° to keep warm.
Pour off fat, retaining enough to cover bottom of pan approximately 1/4 to 1/2 inch deep.
Put onions into hot grease; salt lightly and pepper very generously. Add venison to onions.
Cook, turning venison and stirring onions until venison is partially cooked.
Add red wine and cook until venison is tender.
Put bacon strips on top of onions/venison and serve.
I serve this with mashed potatoes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple. Combine sugar and flour. Add pineapple and cheese. Mix well. Spray 7 x 12 casserole dish with Pam or grease lightly with butter. Add pineapple mixture and top with Ritz cracker crumbs. Pour melted margarine over crumbs and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and garden vegetable twist
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook broccoli and carrots with basil and garlic powder until tender, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and cheese.
Add macaroni and chicken.
Heat through, stirring often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add spices and onion.
Cook for 3 minutes. Set aside to drain.
Mix salsa and tomato sauce together into a bowl.
Spray sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with tortilla. Spread with beans and dollop with sauce, sour cream and shredded cheese.
Place another layer of tortilla.
Put on a layer of meat mixture and repeat with more beans and meat as long as they last. Save enough sauce and Cheddar cheese to top dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: new jersey tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In saucepan, heat soup, milk and cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce, flaked tuna and peas.
In the bottom of a greased bowl, place half of macaroni.
Pour on half of sauce.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix and serve cold.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Empty milk into a large bowl and stir in lemon juice.
Add fruits and Cool Whip; stir well.
Pour into graham cracker crusts and refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: martha stewart's quick cook broccoli soup
directions: In a pot, melt butter.
Add leek, carrot and broccoli.
Cook until tender (5 minutes), but do not brown.
Add stock; simmer. Add broccoli; cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Pour into food processor and process until veggies are finely chopped but not pureed.
Pour soup back into pot.
Stir in cream, cayenne and celery seed. Reheat and serve.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until sauce is thick and bubbly. Add the chicken and mushrooms. Serve on toast.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and shape into a loaf.
Then mix the remaining ingredients and pour over top of ham loaf.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: pierogi(basic dough; polish)
directions: Sift flour and salt in bowl.
Add egg, sour cream and warm water.
Mix together.
Knead dough until smooth.
Divide dough and roll about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in circles.
Fill with one of the following fillings.

title: nestle quik chocolate pie
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and cool about 30 minutes.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Let set in refrigerator until chilled and firm.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut all fruits in small pieces and mix together with nuts. Dredge with flour.
Cream Crisco.
Add sugar gradually, creaming after each addition.
Mix eggs, one at a time, to sugar and Crisco.
Add spices and salt to the fruit mixture.
Now add your blended Crisco, sugar and eggs to fruit and spices.
Add juice as needed.
Mix with hands thoroughly.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Prepare pastry for a double-crust 9-inch pie.
Line 9-inch pie pan with 1/2 of the pastry dough.
Combine pie filling ingredients and pour over pie crust in pan.
Dot with 1 tablespoon oleo. Adjust top pastry; seal well (wrap well now and freeze if desired). Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Heat oil (1-inch) to 350°.
Fry tortilla, turning once until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Spread with refried beans, salsa, cheeses, olives and onions.

title: mushroom and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Cook at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted butter.
Press into glass casserole dish.
Mix powdered sugar and 2 sticks softened butter together and spread over crust.
Slice bananas (long ways) and place over powdered sugar mixture.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple. Sprinkle nuts and cherries on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook and drain ground beef.
Add Ragu. Cook noodles until tender.
Drain.
Mix egg, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese with cottage cheese.
In an 8 x 11 1/2-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 noodles, Ragu mixture, cottage cheese mixture and Mozzarella.
Repeat layers.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions, pepper and celery in saucepan. Drain. Add to cooked rice and canned soup.
Mix well. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple pie
directions: Measure flour and shortening into bowl.
Cut shortening into flour.
When mixed well add water one tablespoon at a time until flour is moistened and dough cleans of side of bowl.
Form into ball on a floured pastry cloth and flatten.
Roll out dough to fit into a pan.
Fold into quarters and unfold in pan.
Sprinkle inside of dough with cinnamon.

title: pasta roll-ups
directions: Warm sauce, stir in 1 cup of grated cheese.
Cover each cooked noodle with 1\3 cup of sauce mixture.
Roll up each noodle and place in 9x13-inch pan.
Spoon remaining sauce over rolled noodles. Top with mozzarella cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 min. to 1 hour.
Cooked Italian Sausages also can be rolled in with noodles.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Boil noodles according to directions on box.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with tomato sauce.
Add 1 layer of noodles.
Sprinkle ground beef, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese on top of noodles.
Continue layering until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover the bottom with a single layer of potatoes.
Sprinkle generously with salt, pepper and flour; add a few dots of butter. Repeat until all potato slices are used.
Pour milk over the potatoes.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake 1 hour.

title: chocolate fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, powder, salt, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Add milk, butter and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Add pecans.
Put into greased shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle over mixture in dish. Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water on top.
Do not mix; leave in layers.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or cold with vanilla ice cream.
When done, it will have chocolate cake on top and chocolate fudge pudding on the bottom.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat oysters in their liquid until they start to curl.
Add salt, pepper, butter and milk.
Heat just until it starts to boil, but do not boil.
Serve with crackers.

title: cherry pecan pound cake
directions: In large bowl beat butter and sugar together at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients except flour. Beat well.
Reduce mixer speed to low and add flour 1/2 cup at a time.
Beat just until blended.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan and spread mixture evenly into it.
Bake at 325° about 60 to 70 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: dorothy's cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Real good.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and add cranberry sauce.
Stir good.
Add other ingredients.
Stir while it jells 1 or 2 times. Refrigerate until time to eat.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken and remove skin and bones, pull a part into bite size pieces.
Steam or microwave broccoli until crunch tender. Grease or spray 9 by 13 inch casserole dish.
Layer chicken and broccoli in dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and dots of butter. Cover lightly with 1/2 grated cheese and sprinkle almonds.	Mix soup, sour cream, remainder of cheese and wine.
Heat until mixed thoroughly.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with almonds, paprika and a wee bit of cayenne.	Bake at 375° until bubbly throughout, approximately 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Place ingredients in order given in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken and vegetable bake
directions: Blend veggies, thawed and drained with soup, milk, salt, chicken, 1/2 cup of cheese and 1/2 can of onions.
Spread mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions on top of dish. Bake 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts and onions are brown.

title: peanut slaw
directions: Mix milk, sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and mayonnaise until well blended.
Toss with cabbage.
Garnish with peanuts.

title: blueberry whipped creme pie
directions: Combine blueberries, sugar, flour and lemon juice in saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until thick.
Remove from heat and cool completely.
