Mix milk, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Pour 1/2 blueberry mixture into cooked and cooled pie crust, then pour 1/2 Cool Whip mixture.
Repeat layers.
Cool. Serve cold.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Melt margarine and cook zucchini and onion in a 10-inch skillet until tender.
Add the next 5 ingredients to mixture.
In bowl, mix eggs and Mozzarella cheese.
Add zucchini, etc., to this and mix. In baking dish, press over bottom and up sides to form crust the dinner rolls.
Dump zucchini and cheese mixture in and bake 18 to 20 minutes in 375° oven.
Knife inserted in middle should come out clean.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening and add milk slowly.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of stew.
Cover tightly and cook 12 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread the tube of sugar cookies as a crust on a 14-inch pizza pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Combine the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla until well blended.
Spread over crust.
Arrange well drained fruit over topping.
Mix a glaze with the water, cornstarch and sugar.
Boil 1 minute and add 1 tablespoon oleo and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool slightly and then brush over top of fruit.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add pineapple, oil, eggs, vanilla and bananas.
Mix until blended by hand.
Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: b l t dip
directions: Toast bread and quarter it.
Serve. Can also be used for chips.
For larger amount, add 1/2 cup more Miracle Whip.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Press butter and vanilla wafers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat together for about 8 minutes butter, confectioners sugar and egg.
Spread over crumbs.
Stir together cranberries, apples, pineapple, sugar and marshmallows and put on creamed mixture.
Top with whipped cream.

title: nonnie's coffee cake
directions: Blend flour, sugars, and shortening.
Reserve 1 1/2 cup of flour mixture for topping.	Add milk and baking soda together until soda is dissolved.	Add to remaining flour mixture, along with eggs, baking powder and salt.
Blend until all is moistened. Batter will be lumpy.
Pour into greased 9 inch x 13 inch pan. Place reserved flour mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: wet chocolate cake
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa, oil and water.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add hot mixture and beat just until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cake will look wet on top.

title: snickerdoole cookies
directions: Blend ingredients together until smooth.
Chill dough for at least 2 hours.
Roll into small balls.
Roll balls into mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and 3 tablespoons cinnamon.
Bake at 400° on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: date ritz crackers
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill 3 hours.
This will keep a long time in the refrigerator.
Spread on Ritz crackers.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°, then cool.
Top with frosting.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Add all at once to flour mixture.
Blend until flour is moistened.
Yields three (9-inch) pie shells.
Can be frozen.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, margarine and sugar.
Add flour and mix well.
Roll out dough and crust into miniature biscuits.
Bake at 425° until golden brown (approximately 15 to 20 minutes).
Serve hot with butter and honey.

title: pecan pie cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, pecans, sugar and butter.
Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: swedish white brownies
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Beat in large bowl.
Add flour, almond flavoring and melted oleo.
Pour into 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with almonds and sugar.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mrs. mcdowell's cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar & brown sugar.
Add eggs & vanilla.
Mix together flour & oatmeal (put small amounts in blender until it turns to powder).
Mix all ingredients then add chocolate chips, hershey bar & nuts.
Roll dough into golf ball sized balls & place on an ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375 for 10-12 minutes.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: tangy vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Good with all vegetables.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease loaf pans.
Combine the first 5 ingredients in large bowl and mix on medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend into egg mixture on low speed.
Add seed and vanilla and beat well until smooth.
Turn into pans and bake until golden and bread tests done, 60 to 65 minutes.
Makes 3 large loaves or 9 mini loaves.

title: old southern corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and sugar in medium bowl; mix well. Add 3 tablespoons bacon drippings, eggs and buttermilk; mix well. Heat remaining 2 tablespoons bacon drippings in 10-inch cast-iron skillet until sizzling hot.
Pour batter into skillet.
Cook over medium heat until batter is bubbly.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: peaches and cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add orange juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Prepare topping mix according to package directions.
Blend in cheese.
Stir in pecans.
Fold into gelatin mixture and pour into an 8 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: good, easy red rice
directions: Brown meat slightly in oleo or bacon drippings. Combine all other ingredients and mix well. Add meat and bacon drippings. Bake, covered, in a baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Stir dry jello into pineapple and mix well.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in buttermilk.
Chill again until partially set.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package in a large bowl.
Add cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Mix with an electric mixer on medium speed.
Set aside.
In a small bowl mix crumbs and butter. Spread 1/2 of the crumb mixture into the bottom of a deep casserole dish, pressing down evenly.
Pour 1/2 of Dream Whip mixture into dish, spreading evenly.
Pour cherry pie filling in next and top with remaining Dream Whip.
Add remaining crumbs to top and chill for 1 hour.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain and mix all vegetables.
Do not put in a metal bowl.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Mix bread crumbs and cheese.
Beat together milk, eggs and salt.
Roll chicken in egg mixture and then in crumb mixture.
Put on greased sheet pan.
Put one generous tablespoon melted margarine on each breast half.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Bottoms will brown more quickly.
Turn if necessary.
If large breasts are used, this will serve 10 to 12.

title: barb's potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine 1/2 margarine with all ingredients, except corn flakes, in a large bowl.
Pour into baking dish.
Mix remaining margarine with corn flakes and top casserole with them.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
Set aside.

title: easy and delicious raspberry trolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl using an electric mixer at medium speed, cream butter with sugar.
Beat in cinnamon and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Using floured hands, pinch off a piece of dough and place 1 inch apart on a large baking sheet.
With your thumb, make a dent in the top of each ball.
Dollop a heaping 1/4 teaspoon raspberry preserves in each dent.
Bake for 12 minutes until the dough is set and preserves are bubbly.
Cool 10 minutes on cookie sheet, then transfer to a rack to cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, nuts, sugar, carrots, egg yolks and hot water.
Sift together dry ingredients and combine with others.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Combine 1 cup sugar and 1 cup orange juice.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cooled cake.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake layers and let cool completely.
Make pudding, put in refrigerator to set.
Place on cake layer in glass bowl.
Put 1/2 pudding on top.
Put other cake layer on top of first layer and remaining pudding on top of second layer.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: crab cheese puffs
directions: Mix crabmeat and cream cheese.
Add garlic powder and salt. Brush wonton skins with egg.
Drop 1 teaspoon filling off center on skin.
Fold into triangle.
Seal and crimp edges.
Brush with egg.
Fry in hot fat for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.

title: age 8 cheese fritters
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, salt and butter.
Sift baking powder with flour.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat well.
Add cheese.
Drop by tablespoon in hot oil.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: wrapped brie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thaw pastry 30 minutes.
Roll sheet out on a lightly floured surface to a 15-inch circle.
Slice chilled Brie in half (horizontally) and layer with almonds. Reassemble and place in center of pastry.
Brush pastry edges with egg wash and pull up sides to enclose Brie.
Place, seam side down, on ungreased baking sheet.
Decorate with a cross of the leftover dough, braided.
Brush with egg wash. Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: perfect frosting
directions: Combine ingredients in mixer bowl.
Blend at low speed, then at high speed until smooth and fluffy, about 5 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: In hot oil in heavy pan, fry garlic and onion until soft.
Add beef; cook and stir until crumbly.
Mix in salt, pepper, rosemary and tomato paste, blended with water.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 400° until done.
Makes 3 dozen muffins.

title: apricot-mandarin sorbet
directions: Drain apricots, reserving 2/3 cup syrup.
In a food processor, puree until smooth, drained apricots, reserved syrup, drained mandarins, egg white and lemon juice.
Pour mixture into a shallow pan and freeze until firm.
Return to processor and again puree until smooth.
Spread in pan again and freeze until firm.
Process and chill a total of 3 times.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Grate the cheese on the large openings of the grater. Lay a large piece of wax paper on the counter first, then start this process: put down layer of grated cheese, mayonnaise, some pimentos and a handful of pickles. Fold it over and over, starting from the bottom layer. The repeat the process and fold again and do this until you have used all your ingredients. Put in jars and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl (you may have to knead with your hands).
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce (or spaghetti sauce). Season to taste.
Add onions and bell peppers.
Layer uncooked lasagna noodles, Mozzarella, Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheeses, sauce, cottage or Ricotta cheese, topping with Parmesan.
Repeat layers until top, ending with sauce and leftover cheeses.
Add 1/2 cup of water, pouring around the edges.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese on top is brown, in 350° oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add 1 box strawberry jello (small) and mix together.
Cool, then add 4 or 5 cups of strawberries.
Stir together.
Pour into cooked pie shells and top with whipped cream.
Let this set in refrigerator before cutting. If frozen strawberries are used, let thaw slightly and drain juice out before using.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Put in 9 or 10-inch square pan in the order in which it is listed.
Do not stir.
Be sure to cover all ingredients when pouring on the sweet milk.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: hello dolly
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer crumbs, coconut, chips and pecans.
Pour 1 can Eagle Brand milk on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Mix altogether and simmer for about 1 hour.

title: mom's cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in milk, sugar, butter, salt, eggs and 2 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth and then gradually add rest of flour until smooth and elastic.
Cover; let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch; let rise again. Divide dough in half.
Roll out into 15 x 9-inch size.
Spread with butter and sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll and cut.
Put in greased pans.
Repeat with other half of dough.
Let rise again 40 minutes.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Frost with powdered sugar frosting while warm.

title: venison steak
directions: Cut venison into 1-inch thick slices.
Brush with soy sauce. Sprinkle with garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Dredge lightly in flour.
Brown steak on both sides in hot oil in a large skillet. Transfer to a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and set aside.
Drain drippings from skillet.
Add margarine.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly to loosen particles.
Stir in water and cook until heated.
Pour over steak.
Put onion over steak.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crepes a la bananas foster
directions: Note:
Prepared crepes can often be located in freezer department of stores.
If not available, serve sundae style.

title: broccoli hash brown quiche
directions: Press the hash browns onto the bottom and up the sides of a greased 9 inch pie plate, forming a shell.
Sprinkle with broccoli.
In a bowl, beat eggs, sour cream and salt.
Stir in cheese and pour over broccoli.

title: the cherry thing
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam.
Put cherry pie filling in pan, then pour crushed pineapple over the cherries.
Spread evenly over pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the cherries and pineapple as evenly as you can.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle the nuts over the cake mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° and 10 minutes at 375° or until done.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine rice, soup and chicken.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until brown and hot.

title: beet salad
directions: Heat beet juice to boiling.
Add to boiling water, then to lemon jello.
Pour into mold and set.
Very attractive at Christmas.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake according to box directions.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with margarine and milk; spread over hot cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, then nuts.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer at 350°.
These are excellent!!

title: apple jacks
directions: Put apples in pot with about 3 inches of water.
Cook on low heat until tender.
Remove apples from heat and add sugar and spices.
Do not drain.
Let cool.
Let biscuits come to room temperature.
Sprinkle flour on wax paper.
Roll biscuit until size of hand.
Cover one side of dough with apples, fold and pinch edges together.
Do this for each biscuit.
Fry in margarine until brown on both sides.
Add margarine as needed, cook slow.

title: thad's door slammer chicken
directions: Blend ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for the first 45 minutes, then uncover and bake 50 minutes more.

title: pumpernickel bread dip
directions: Chill overnight before serving for best taste.
Hollow out inside of bread to make a bowl.
Cut up pieces into bite size pieces.
Place each half of bread on platter.
Fill each section with sour cream mixture.
Place cut pieces of bread around the bread on platter.
Dip bread pieces into mixture.
You may also cut up celery, cucumbers or anything you may like and place on platter with the bread pieces.
When the bread is empty, cut into bite size pieces, also.

title: mexican cabbage
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients and drain.
Add other ingredients and cook until cabbage is done.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on box and spread over 11 x 13-inch nonstick jelly roll baking pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
If toothpick is wet, bake a few more minutes.
While brownie mix is baking, prepare sauce (icing).
In saucepan, mix water and margarine.
Heat until margarine melts.
Add cocoa, vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Stir and make sauce thick enough to spoon or pour over brownies.
If too thick to pour, add water until desired thickness is obtained. Remove brownies from oven when done.
Spread marshmallows over brownies.
Return brownies (with marshmallows) to oven for 1 to 2 minutes.
Do not leave brownies in oven too long or they will be too hard to cut.
Remove brownies/marshmallows from oven and pour icing over hot marshmallow.
Swirl in with spoon.
Sprinkle pecan pieces over icing, if desired.
Let cool.
Cut, eat and enjoy.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Mix with hands, roll out and bake about 20 minutes at 300°. Roll in powdered sugar and bake again 20 more minutes.

title: granny denton's rolls
directions: Cover first three ingredients with boiling water and cool. When lukewarm, add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and let stand until doubled in bulk.
Work down and knead well and make into rolls.
Let rise again.
Cook at 400° until brown as you like.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together stuffing mix and oleo.
Press all but 1 cup in dish.
Mix together and heat soups and milk.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour over stuffing.
Top with remaining cup of stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix. Spread this mixture on top of the nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a greased pan.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with croutons.
Place sausage and cheese on top.
Mix eggs and milk and pour on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken adobo
directions: In a saucepan, combine vinegar, garlic, pepper, bay leaves and soy sauce.
Put in chicken to soak for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add water and simmer, uncovered, until tender.
Serve with rice.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven
to
In a large plastic bag or bowl combine oil
and
soup mix.
Add potatoes, peeled or unpeeled. Stir or shake
in
bag until evenly coated.
Put potatoes in a shallow
roasting
pan.
Bake,
stirring
occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Add the eggs and mix well. Sift the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt and add to the creamed mixture.
Add the apples and nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop corn and place in large brown paper bag; set aside.
May add 2 cups of peanuts.
Combine sugar, butter, Karo and salt in 2-quart glass bowl.
Mix well and microwave on High setting for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after each minute, until it begins to boil. Cook 2 minutes more.
Stir in soda and mix well (will foam). Quickly pour in paper bag over the corn.
Shake well and cook another 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake thoroughly and empty in a large pan to cool.

title: overnight french toast
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour in melted butter; sprinkle sugar over top of butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Lay bread over mixture.
Blend eggs and milk.
Pour evenly over bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice with vegetables
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water; bring water to a boil. Add rice and cook 15 minutes.
In pan, saute onion, green pepper, celery and carrot in butter.
When rice is cooked, mix the rice with the sauteed vegetables.
Add salt, pepper and paprika or spices as desired.

title: rainbow crayons(child-approved)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line each muffin cup with a separate piece of foil.
Child takes all paper off crayons.
Breaks crayons into 1-inch pieces (approximately).
Put crayons into each foil-lined muffin cup (cups should be about half full of loosely piled crayons).

title: fruit crumble
directions: Put pie filling in big dish.
Mix all other ingredients and put on top.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 1 hour.

title: crackerjack cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Add and sift flour, soda and baking powder.
Mix in oatmeal, coconut and cereal.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: escarole and beans
directions: In a large saucepan place chicken broth and escarole, bring to a boil and simmer 1 hour.
Brown garlic in olive oil gently and add cannellini beans with liquid.
Combine with escarole and let simmer 10 to 20 minutes.
Stir carefully with wooden spoon.
This should have a soupy consistency.
If needed, add more broth.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and serve with hot Italian bread.

title: sunburst muffins
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and pour in greased miniature tins, filling cups 2/3 full.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: "spaghetti casserole"
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and set aside. Saute onions and green pepper in butter (oleo) until tender. Add mushroom soup, olives and tomatoes; simmer 10 minutes. Add chestnuts. Spread half spaghetti in well buttered casserole, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Top with half sauce and half cheese; repeat. Combine mushroom soup with water; mix and pour over casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with green salad.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use dip with fresh carrot sticks, celery sticks, broccoli, cauliflower, etc.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion. Drain. Mix all ingredients. Bake 45 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg yolks, margarine and buttermilk.
Beat egg whites until fluffy and dry, fold into batter. Place 1 small ladle full of batter on hot waffle iron for one waffle.

title: banana lumpia
directions: Thaw lumpia wrappers to the point where they can easily be separated.
Peel plantains and slice in half and then lengthwise (so there will be 4 pieces).
Place 2 plantains in each lumpia wrapper.
Sprinkle plantains with brown sugar (to taste), then wrap and tuck in ends.
Mix egg whites together.
Dip fingertips in egg whites and apply thin layer to exposed edge of wrapper.
Heat oil to high in deep fryer and place lumpia in; cook until golden brown. Drain.
Allow to cool slightly.
Eat while warm.

title: party balls
directions: Mix well.
Form into small balls.
Roll in coconut or leave plain.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: blueberry boy-bait
directions: With pastry blender cut in flour, sugar and butter.
Reserve 3/4 cup for topping.
Add baking powder, salt, eggs and milk to remaining batter and beat for 3 minutes.
Spread batter in greased pan.
Spread fresh or frozen blueberries on top of batter. Sprinkle blueberries with the reserved 3/4 cup for topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: robert's breakfast sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add one cup water and mix well. You can make sausage patties or stuff in sheep casing.
Cook like you would any other sausage or freeze in serving size portions.

title: raisin spice coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Beat all ingredients, except raisins and streusel, on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally for 2 minutes.
Stir in raisins.

title: angel-strawberry bavarian
directions: Cut cake into 1-inch cubes.
In small bowl, combine jello and boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Drain strawberries, reserving juice.
Add enough water to strawberry juice to make 1 cup.
Stir in jello.
Refrigerate until jello is slightly thickened.
Beat jello until foamy.
Fold one cup whipping cream into jello along with strawberries.
Alternate layer of cake cubes and strawberry mixture in 10-inch tube pan.
Unmold cake onto serving plate.
Mix together 1 1/2 cups whipping cream, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Frost sides and top of cake. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: striped bass fillets
directions: Boil bones and trimming of fish to obtain stock.
Wash and dry fillets.
Season with salt.
Place in a saucepan which has been well buttered.
Add finely chopped shallots and coarse chopped parsley.
Moisten with wine, fish stock or water and lemon juice. Cover saucepan and cook 10 minutes.
Remove fillets.
Arrange them upon a long platter or oval dish and keep in a warm place.
Reduce juice of the fish until there is 4 teaspoons left.
Remove fillets. Add butter.
Shake pan to sauce will cover consistency.
Rectify seasoning.
Pour sauce over fillets and glaze in the oven.

title: dumb little dump cake
directions: Read directions before starting!!!

title: ruby's breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Set in refrigerator overnight. Pour into casserole dish; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: our good fruitcake
directions: Mix fruit and 1 cup of flour, then set aside.
Beat margarine, then add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs and lemon extract. Gradually add sifted flour and baking powder.
Add floured fruit to egg mixture and put into greased and floured tube pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Put a pan of water in the oven while cake bakes.
Uncover for last 5 minutes to brown.
Let cake cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Add onion to spinach and cook as directed.
Drain well. Cool slightly.
Beat
eggs
and mix into spinach.
Add cheese and
sour cream;
mix.
Pour
into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.	Serves 12.

title: almond chicken salad
directions: Toast almonds in butter.
Mix all other ingredients together and sprinkle almonds on top.
Can be served plain or on lettuce leaves.
Also 1/4 teaspoon of curry powder may be used for flavor.

title: low-fat apple crisp
directions: Mix together apple filling, water and granulated sugar.
In another bowl mix together dry ingredients.
Fold the two mixtures together and spoon into a 9-inch square baking dish that has been sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 40 minutes until set and golden brown on top.
Serves 9; 1/2 gram fat per serving and 210 calories.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake (chocolate)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Make a well. Pour in rest of ingredients.
Mix all together until well blended, about 5 minutes.
This will be a runny batter when mixed.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and use with veggies to dip.

title: oven hash
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and 1 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Put into 1-quart casserole.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cook and stir meat until done. Drain meat. Cook macaroni as directed on package. Drain. Mix remaining ingredients. Pour in ungreased casserole dish. Cover. Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: antipasto
directions: Slice and cook carrots and celery until tender but firm.
Boil ketchup, oil, vinegar and anchovies for 5 minutes, then add celery and carrots, olives, onions, tuna, pickle, mushrooms, green pepper and salt and pepper.

title: janet smith's green chili rice
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in loaf casserole at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly.
Recipe may be doubled and baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: california wine ice
directions: Add sugar and water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Turn up heat and bring mixture to a boil. Lower heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour syrup into a large container and cool completely.
Add wine, orange juice and lemon juice.
Stir with a whisk.
Pour mixture into a cake pan or roasting pan; place it in the freezer.
Once every hour, stir the mixture with a fork.
After 5 to 6 hours the wine mixture will start to form small crystals and have the consistency of soft sherbet.
(It should have a granular texture.)
Serve a mound of the wine ice in a stemmed wine glass.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix water, yeast, sugar, salt, eggs and shortening.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Let rise to double.
Work down and pinch off to form rolls.
Let rise and bake at 425° until brown.

title: easy potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes.
Combine all ingredients with potatoes and toss lightly.

title: sparkling summer punch
directions: Combine orange juice, apple juice and mint tea in a large pitcher.
Stir until blended well.
Add club soda when ready to serve.

title: potato crust quiche
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and press into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes until potato edges brown a little bit.
Decrease oven to 350°.
Mix next 6 ingredients together.
When crust is done, pour mixture on top and bake another 35 minutes or until set.

title: hot sausage casserole
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking power, eggs, buttermilk and sugar to make batter.
Mix well.
Brown sausage with onion and drain.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a hot, greased, 10-inch iron skillet.
Pour cream-style corn on top of batter.
Add sausage on top of corn.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with remaining batter. Bake until golden brown at 425°.
Good during cool weather!

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and crumbs.
Pour into casserole.
Blend cracker crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle on top. Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, soda and buttermilk.
Beat eggs; add to flour mixture.
Add with boiled mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.

title: oven barbecued steaks
directions: Cut meat into 10 serving pieces.
In skillet, brown meat in oil; remove meat to Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients to skillet; simmer 5 minutes.
Pour catsup mixture over meat.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir sauce and turn pieces after first hour.
Makes 10 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix with melted margarine.
Add 1/2 cup evaporated milk and mix well.
Spread 1/2 batter in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Spread over baked batter. Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over caramel.
Drop remaining batter by spoonfuls over chips and nuts.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: tomato soup molded salad
directions: Heat the soup to boiling.
Remove from heat. Add mashed cream cheese and beat well with mixer until well blended.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix well and let stand, covered, for at least 24 hours.
Hint: Home canned green beans are too soft.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix crumbs and 1/2 cup melted margarine; spread over a
9 x 13-inch pan.

title: deep dish georgia peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg in mixing bowl.
Toss with peaches till well coated.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Carefully stir in grenadine and lemon juice.
Turn mixture into 8x8x2 inch baking dish or deep 9 inch round baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Roll pastry to 10 inch circle and place over peaches.
Cut slits for steam to escape.
Bake at 375° for 50-60 minutes.
Can also bake as regular 2 crust pie.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Cook beef until brown.
Add peppers, onions and celery; cook until limp.
Stir rest of ingredients in; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add meat sauce to beans; mix lightly.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese and melt.

title: glorious morning muffin(low cholesterol)
directions: Combine
bran,	baking powder, cinnamon, nuts, allspice and soda.
Add	remaining
ingredients.
Stir
only until just well combined.
Spoon
into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Watch closely so they don't scorch.

title: mother's foolproof pie crust
directions: With a fork, mix together first 4 ingredients.
In separate dish, beat 1/2 cup water, egg and vinegar.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Add water as needed.
Then shape into 4 or 5 balls. Chill at least 15 minutes.
(Dough can be frozen for use later. Thaw and work with it while still cold.)

title: muffin toppers
directions: Thoroughly blend butter and mustard.
Spread on muffin halves. Divide ham between muffins.
Top with cheese.
Place on microproof plate.
Cook on 50% for 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Put the pimento cheese into a 1-quart bowl.
Measure the mayonnaise and add to the pimento cheese.
Add the minced onions; stir in the horseradish.
Add the Tabasco sauce and pinch of garlic salt.
Add the frozen salad shrimp.
Stir all ingredients and mix well.
Put in refrigerator.
Let set for 2 hours before serving.

title: harvest cider
directions: Stir cider, sugar and lemon juice until sugar is dissolved and chill.
Right before serving, add 1 quart ginger ale.
Yield: 13 cups.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir together flour with ground oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda. Stir into creamed butter and sugar.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Dice large amount of apples and press firmly into cake batter in cake pan.
Cover with 1 c. sugar, 2 Tbsp flour, 2 Tbsp melted butter and cinnamon.
Bake 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana split pie(makes two pies)
directions: Cream/smash butter and Philadelphia cream cheese until smooth, then add powdered sugar (2 cups).
Put in pie crust.
Drain pineapple.
Clean and slice strawberries.
Spread pineapple over pie crust.
Use a half can of pineapple for each pie.
Spread strawberries.
Add sliced bananas.
Add Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: peach delight
directions: Spread 1 can of rolls in bottom of pan. Mix together cream cheese and sugar and spread on top. Spread pie filling on top. Layer the other can of rolls on top. Melt butter and drizzle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Spread evenly in thin layer on a dinner size plate.
Cover cream cheese with cocktail sauce.
Drain shrimp and spread over sauce.
Chill.
Spread with knife on crackers.

title: layered mexican dip(low-fat)
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain thoroughly.
Set aside.
Spray skillet with butter flavored cooking spray.
Brown diced onion. Add cooked ground beef.
Stir refried beans into beef mixture. Spray a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish with cooking spray.
Spread beef and bean mixture evenly in pan.
Sprinkle green chilies over top of mixture.
Spread half of cheese over this.
Pour taco sauce over cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly and spread sour cream to make a cross on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 9.
Contains about 1 gram of fat per serving.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and melted margarine to flour mixture and mix thoroughly with electric mixer or by hand.
Add nuts by folding into other mixture.
Place in 13 1/2 x 9-inch baking pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool in pan before cutting into squares. Yields 30 (1/2-inch) squares.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and hot sausage; add chopped onions and peppers.
Drain off grease, then mix with Prego spaghetti sauce. Cook lasagna noodles in boiling water for 10 to 15 minutes.
Layer your casserole dish with meat sauce, noodles, and cheeses.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: "fat-free" creme caramel
directions: Very lightly spray four ramekin or custard cups with Pam cooking spray.
Place 1 ounce of maple syrup in the bottom of each cup, and place them in a freezer.
Dissolve gelatin in 4 ounces of liquid and set aside.
Combine balance of ingredients in a 1-quart saucepan and bring to a boil while stirring constantly.
Mixture will burn easily.
Remove from heat and stir in dissolved gelatin. Remove custard cups from freezer and fill with mixture. Refrigerate for two hours or longer.
To serve, invert custard cup onto flat dish and serve at once.

title: speedy shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a wide shallow pan and place tails up in pan.
Bake for 2 minutes.
Remove from oven and set aside.
Melt butter; don't boil.
Add shallots, garlic, lemon juice, A.1., Worcestershire sauce, tarragon and pepper.
Remove from stove.
Let cool.
Stir often until butter stiffens and ingredients are well blended.
Spread the mix over shrimp.
Place shrimp under a preheated broiler for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with hot garlic bread and wedges of lemon.
Serves 2.

title: chicken slices "pollo en rajas"
directions: Cut chicken into long strips and season with salt and pepper on both sides.
Saute until golden; set aside.
In 2 teaspoons olive oil, saute onions.
Add chicken strips; cover and turn heat to low. In a baking dish (sprayed with Pam), layer beginning with green chilies, jalapeno pepper, onions and top with chicken.
Begin layering again.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Spread soft cream cheese into the bottom of a baked pie shell about 1/4-inch thick.
Fill pie shell with fresh raspberries.
In saucepan, mix together ingredients.
Bring to a boil and stir, boiling 1 to 2 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour over raspberries. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter.
Cook broccoli.
Add soup and cheese. Stir until melted.
Add pepper, Accent and nuts.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Heat in oven thoroughly.
Freezes nicely.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: 7-layer surprise
directions: In a greased 13 x 9-inch pan, add all ingredients in order. Dot top with the 1 stick of margarine.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 15-inch buttered pan.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: muffins mcmullen
directions: Brown sausage with chopped green pepper and onion.
Drain grease.
Add olives, chopped tomato and mushrooms.
Keep warm. Place opened muffins on cookie sheet under broiler until crisp. Spoon mix onto muffins; cover with Swiss cheese and bake at 300° until cheese melts.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken; set aside.
Use 2 cups or more of broth and flour; mix to consistency you can roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Add soup to leftover chicken broth.
Boil.
While at a boil, drop in cut up dumplings.
When done, add cooked, deboned chicken.
Serve.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Add water if needed during cooking.
Cook garlic, onion, celery and pepper in bacon drippings and olive oil over medium heat until tender, but not brown.
Add everything else but shrimp. Simmer 3 or 4 hours, stirring every now and then.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and reduce to simmer, about 5 minutes.
Serve over yellow rice.
All you need is Cuban bread and tossed salad. Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Place in greased Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: italian spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Cook onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil until clear.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook with lid off center for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add meat balls.
Cook 1 more hour.

title: sweet and sour glazed chicken wings
directions: Rinse chicken and drain.
Combine glaze ingredients in large bowl.
Add chicken and toss lightly to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°. Arrange chicken, skin side down, on baking plan lined with aluminum foil.
Bake 25 minutes; turn over.
Bake another 25 minutes or until a deep golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: broccoli casserole supreme
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in oiled casserole.
Top with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: louisiana stew
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Working in small batches, brown chicken pieces on all sides, then drain on paper towel.
Stir-fry onion, celery and peppers 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, lemon juice, hot pepper sauce, bay leaves, broth, garlic, salt and pepper.
Bring to a simmer.
Add chicken to pan; simmer, uncovered, for about 30 minutes.
Add sausage and cook another 30 minutes.
Skim off any fat.
Remove any bones.
Serve in shallow soup bowls over freshly cooked rice or as a stew.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Combine vegetables in saucepan and cook until nearly done. Melt butter in medium saucepan; stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk; stir constantly.
When mixture becomes thick, add cheese (cubed) and stir until melted.
Add vegetables and pepper to taste, mixing well.
Heat thoroughly.
For a thinner soup, add more milk.

title: tomato ice salad
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Combine sugar and 1 cup water in saucepan.
Boil about 5 minutes, until light syrup.
Add fruit juices, tomato sauce and gelatin to syrup.
Remove from heat.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Pour into tray.
Freeze until mushy, then whip until light and airy.
Fold in egg whites. Return to freezer until served.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta, eggs, pepper, grated cheese, nutmeg and parsley in large bowl.
Add vegetables and salt in other bowl.
Cook noodles according to directions on box.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: If you can't find French vanilla pudding mix, add 2 teaspoons vanilla.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Store in airtight container. Serve 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot or boiling water.
Garnish with marshmallows.

title: chow-chow
directions: Prepare tomatoes, cabbages, peppers and onions, chopped finely.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil; put in scalded jars and seal.

title: turkey drops
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butterscotch chips.
When melted, mix with bag of chow mein noodles and drop onto wax paper. When cool, you can eat.
Um-m good!

title: seafood au gratin
directions: In a 1-quart casserole stir soup until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Mix in seafood and parsley.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos.
Cream together cream cheese, oleo and powdered sugar.
Mix together milk, pudding and whipped topping.
Blend 2 mixes.
Layer into clean flower pot.
Start and end with cookies. May decorate with artificial flowers or use child's sand pail and shovel.

title: hot wings
directions: Deep fry wings to desired degree of crispness.
Drain well. Shake in paper grocery bag.
When wings are almost done, slowly heat sauce until butter just melts.
Stir sauce until blended. Turn heat off.
Put wings in large mixing bowl.
Spoon sauce over wings.
Toss wings until coated with sauce.
Enjoy.

title: mom's apple pie
directions: *Make your own or use Pillsbury.

title: hot asparagus dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: soldier's fudge
directions: Butter 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Heat milk, unsweetened chocolate and chocolate chips in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread mixture in pan.
Refrigerate until firm, at least 1 hour.

title: divinity
directions: Put sugar, water, salt and syrup into medium size saucepan over hot heat.
Bring to a boil and cover just long enough for sugar to dissolve.
Beat egg whites until stiff (all the time the syrup is cooking).
Cook syrup to the hard boil stage.
Pour stage half over the egg whites, beating steadily.
Cook the other half of the syrup until it spins a thread, then pour over the other and beat until it starts to lose its shine and hold its shape.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and let stand.

title: cajun salad
directions: Drain
pineapple
and oranges.
Add lemon juice and soak sliced bananas for about 10 minutes.
Drain bananas and mix all together.

title: pinwheel meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, half of the process cheese spread, egg and salt; mix together.
Pat out meat mixture to cover a 12 x 10-inch rectangle of waxed paper.
Cook rice according to directions and combine with remaining process cheese spread and parsley. Spread over meat. Roll up, starting at narrow end. Wrap roll securely in waxed paper and foil.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Cut into slices.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until meat is done.

title: ricotta pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks with 5 tablespoons sugar and the coffees.
Add Ricotta and mix well.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks, gradually adding 3 tablespoons sugar. Fold cream into Ricotta mixture, then fold in egg whites.
Turn into a 7-inch mold that has been moistened inside with water and refrigerate for several hours.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion.
Add tomato sauce and chili beans.
Sprinkle top of chili with pepper, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco to taste.
Add sliced green pepper.

title: italian banana pepper casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and set aside.
Remove seeds from peppers and cut into big chunks.

Combine ground beef, peppers, rice, spaghetti sauce, 1 cup cheese and mushrooms in casserole dish. Top with remaining cheese and bake in covered dish until last 15 minutes at 350° for 30 minutes or until peppers are nice and tender.

title: easy shrimp creole
directions: In large skillet, put olive oil and saute onion, green pepper and celery.
Add the remaining ingredients except the shrimp. Stir all ingredients until heated thoroughly.
Lastly, add shrimp and simmer until shrimp turn pink.
Serve over rice.

title: really excellent pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend until well mixed.
(The blender eliminates the need to mash the pumpkin.)
Put in a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then turn down to 375° and bake 50 minutes more.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together and place in crust; refrigerate.

title: white bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine 5 cups of flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
In saucepan, heat water, milk and shortening until warm (120° to 130°).
Shortening does not need to melt.
Add to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.

title: bacon cheese appetizer
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and crumbly. Mix with cheese and green onions. Combine all with mayonnaise and horseradish to taste. Spread on party rye and bake at 350° until cheese melts (about 10 minutes).

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add marshmallows. Mix cream cheese and drained pineapple.
Whip partly set Jell-O with mixer until creamy looking.
Add cream cheese and pineapple mixture with Jell-O.
Fold in carton of Cool Whip.

title: german chocolate frosting
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients, stirring frequently (about 12 minutes); might burn.
Cook until thick.
Add coconut and pecans.

title: new england veggies
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Set aside.
In a 2 quart casserole melt butter in microwave on High 30 to 60 seconds.
Stir in cornstarch and microwave on High an additional 1 to 2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds until butter is slightly thickened.
Add veggies, garlic salt and cheese.
Heat on High in microwave 10 minutes, stirring twice.
Serves 8.

title: continental chicken strips
directions: In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise, mustard, sugar and vinegar until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate sauce.
Cut chicken into thin 3 x 1-inch strips.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place flour, egg and bread crumbs in separate shallow dishes.
Coat chicken pieces with flour, shaking off excess.
Dip into egg, then coat with crumbs, set aside.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, melt enough shortening to measure 1/4 inch.
When hot, fry half of the chicken until golden brown, turning once during cooking.
Drain on paper towels.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Sprinkle paprika on mustard sauce.
Serve with hot chicken strips.
Makes about 22 pieces.

title: peanut butter, jelly and mustard sandwich
directions: Put jelly and peanut butter on 1 slice of bread and mustard on the other slice.
Place together to make sandwich.
Don't be afraid to try it.
It's really good.
You can add more of the last three items to suit your taste.

title: mexicali dip
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic.
Crumble beef. Stir in all remaining ingredients except raisins.
Stirring occasionally, bring mixture to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in raisins. Serve warm with cheese sprinkled on top.
Use as a dip for tortilla chips and/or raw vegetable dippers.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add more flour until dough is not sticky.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Moisten graham cracker crumbs and 4 tablespoons sugar with butter.
Mix together and place in bottom of small cupcake pan. Combine first four ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into cups over crumbs.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed head lettuce
directions: Wash head of lettuce and remove core.
With a tablespoon, remove enough of the lettuce around the core to leave a cavity (2 to 3 inches) in the center of the head.
Combine other ingredients listed and pack mixture firmly in cavity of lettuce.
Cover and chill until center is solid.
To serve, slice crosswise and add a little French dressing.

title: connie's cheesecakes
directions: Put vanilla wafers in cupcake or muffin pan (be sure to use cupcake liners).
Whip remaining ingredients until smooth.
Drop mixture on top of wafers.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool and top with pie filling of your choice.
Refrigerate.

title: crusty pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add flour and eggs alternately, beating after each addition.
Add flavoring.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: onion soup
directions: Simmer beef broth in saucepan on low, while preparing onions. Peel onions and slice thinly.
Separate slices into rings.
Saute onion rings in hot butter in skillet until softened.
Lightly stir in flour.
Add cooked onions to simmering broth.
Cover and simmer another 20 minutes.
Ladle soup into bowls.
Place a round of bread on soup.
Sprinkle with combined cheeses.
Place bowls on cookie sheet and brown cheese under preheated broiler for 3 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.
Serve immediately.

title: no knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and half the flour.
Beat thoroughly.
Add beaten egg and shortening. Gradually add rest of the flour.
Cover and put in refrigerator about 2 hours before using.
Take out what is needed.
Return rest to refrigerator and punch down everyday, even if none is used. Let rest 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake 12 to 18 minutes in 400° oven.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix and put in 4 or 5 small rolls.
Roll in plastic wrap. Freeze or refrigerate 24 hours.
Slice thin (about 1/4-inch) and bake at 350° approximately 8 or 9 minutes.
Be careful not to overbake.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form into a ball.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans according to package directions.
Drain well.
Mix beans and soup.
Place in casserole.
Top with French fried onion rings.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken biscuit casserole
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, flour, onion and milk.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Blend in 1 cup cheese until melted.
Stir in peas, chicken, pimento, salt and pepper.
Heat through.
Place in 8 or 9-inch baking dish.
Place biscuits on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer, until golden brown.

title: farmers' corn cakes
directions: Stir
together	flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt. Set aside.
In another bowl blend eggs, milk and butter together.
Add to
flour mixture; stir just until moistened. (Batter will be lumpy.)
Gently
fold in corn.
To cook pour about 1/4 cup	of batter into a hot lightly greased skillet.	Cook until golden brown on both sides.

title: brownies
directions: Combine eggs and sugar, then add flour, cocoa, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Add melted butter last.
Pour into buttered pie pan and bake about 20 minutes at 375°.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Combine and mix well by hand.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Combine.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Roll in balls.
Roll in 2 parts sugar and 2 parts cinnamon.
Bake at 350° or 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: hearty turkey chili
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and garlic in oil.
Add turkey and cook until brown.
Add everything but the beans.
Cook 45 minutes, covered (simmer), then add beans and simmer about 15 minutes.

title: garden fresh potatoes with cheese
directions: Place
potatoes and water in 3-quart pan until potatoes are tender;
drain.
Heat
process cheese spread according to label directions.
Gently
stir together the potatoes, cheese mixture and
vegetables in a 3-quart casserole.
Microwave on High
to 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: velvet pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk.
Mix well but do not overbeat.
Add flavorings.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 to 1 1/3 hours.

title: caponata
directions: Wash and dry eggplant.
Leave unpeeled.
Cut in 1-inch cubes; sprinkle with salt.
In a 12-inch skillet, heat oil.
Add eggplant and cook over moderate heat, stirring often until browned and almost tender.
Drain on paper towels.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion in skillet; drain. Add other ingredients and bake for 30 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Add next 5 ingredients. Chill overnight.
The next day, add ginger ale and serve.

title: chicken and rice(serves 4.)
directions: Place chicken pieces (enough to serve 4) in an 8 x 12-inch casserole pan.
Cover chicken with Italian dressing.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove chicken from pan.
Place rice in drippings in pan.
On top of rice, place frozen vegetables. Mix Italian seasonings with chicken broth or bouillon and put over rice and vegetables . Place chicken over rice mixture.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix bran, sugar, flour, baking soda and salt in a large bowl. Mix together and then add to the bran mixture the corn oil, eggs and buttermilk.
Stir all well.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
(The dough can be refrigerated for up to 6 weeks.)
Can do ahead.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: candy coated walnuts
directions: Cook slowly until syrup boils, then boil 3 minutes.
Add nuts. Take off heat and let set for 1 minute.
Then dump out onto wax paper.
Let cool for 10 minutes and break apart.

title: lentil and brown rice soup
directions: In large pot, combine all ingredients. Bring to boil, reduce heat and cover the pan.
Simmer 45 to 55 minutes until lentils and rice are tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Line muffin tins with foil liners (1 5/8 - 2-inch diameter).

title: strawberry cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add Cool Whip, sour cream, sugar and lemon juice, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Top with strawberries.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let brown in oven, then cover with foil for remainder of time.

title: cajun baked ham
directions: Remove skin from ham.
Place ham on foil in baking dish. Spread mustard over ham.
Pour honey over mustard.
Wrap ham in foil and seal loosely.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve the sauce with the ham slices.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Refrigerate cauliflower and broccoli in a bowl.
Mix the remaining ingredients and add cauliflower and broccoli just before serving.

title: quick chicken and noodles
directions: Cook, drain and set aside noodles.
In a large saucepan, combine soups, milk, seasoned salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add drained chicken.
Add noodles. Drain carrots and add to chicken and noodles.
Toss gently. Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: lima bean stew with meatballs
directions: Pour beans into large dutch oven; add the 4 1/2 c. water and boil 2 minutes.
Combine flour and the cold water.
Stir into the beans; cook until thickened and bubbly. Add vegetables, bay leaf and the 2 tsp. salt.
Bring to boiling.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.

title: 3 step cheesecake(preparation time: 10 minutes.  cooking time: 40 minutes.)
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add egg; mix until blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set; cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with fruit and serve.

title: banana slush
directions: Heat sugar and water to boil.
Add lemonade and juice, banana and as many strawberries or raspberries as you wish.
Freeze in an ice cream pail.
Spoon slush in glasses.
Add 7-Up.
(Put in amount of slush and 7-Up you want.)

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Mix up vanilla pudding and keep in refrigerator until ready to use.
Make cake mix and bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
When it comes out of the oven, poke holes all over cake with fork and pour juice from pineapple over cake.

title: banana split pie(low calorie)
directions: Layer pie in the order listed and chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion well. Add rest of ingredients. Mix. Let simmer 15 minutes. Turn into a greased casserole. Top with cornbread topping.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease or spray cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients and roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet spaced 2 inches apart.
Press each ball with a fork.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: granny's frozen dessert
directions: Dissolve sugar and water over heat.
Pour water and sugar over fruit mixture.
Add crushed pineapple.
Put in deep refrigerator tray and freeze.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pan.
Cover tightly; let stand, then bake in 2 casseroles at 275° for 5 hours.
Freeze one of the casseroles.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and ground beef in oil.
Then add remaining ingredients, except spaghetti and cheese.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Mix with cooked spaghetti.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large mixing bowl, add flour, oats, brown sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Put this mixture to the side.
In another bowl, beat egg.
Add milk and oil. Stir in raisins.
Mix both mixtures together; batter will be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake until muffins are golden brown (about 20 to 25 minutes).
Let cool about 5 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes about 12.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Put lemon juice on bananas to keep from turning brown.
Mix first 4 ingredients and one half of Cool Whip.
Line the bottom of large glass dish with vanilla wafers and 1/2 of pudding.
Top with bananas and half of Cool Whip.
Make second layer and top with Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: mounds bars
directions: In double boiler, melt together and spread over baked mixture. Cool and refrigerate.
Cut into bars.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Fry pork chops; save drippings.
Dice cooked chops.
Boil rice with onions, peppers and celery; drain, then brown lightly.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder, soy sauce and pork.
Fry 4 to 8 minutes.

title: lea's swedish meat balls
directions: In large bowl, mix ground beef, pork, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into 64 balls, walnut size.
In skillet, heat cooking oil; add half meat balls.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes or until no pink remains, turning to brown them evenly.
Reserve drippings in skillet.
In small bowl, stir together sour cream, flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add water.
Mix well. Stir mixture into drippings; heat until gravy is thickened and bubbly.
Add meat balls to gravy in skillet; heat through.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Heat oil, salt and pepper in deep skillet.
Add celery, onion and water chestnuts and let fry for 5 minutes or so.
Add bean sprouts and stir in chicken broth.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Add to vegetable mixture and stir until mixture thickens.
Add chicken.
Heat through.
Serve over hot chow mein noodles.
Serves 4.
(Stores in refrigerator well for a day or two.)

title: corn "oysters"(makes 4 servings)
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, milk and egg in blender or food processor.
Whirl just until smooth.
Transfer to bowl.
Stir in corn.
Pour 1 tablespoon of the oil into large nonstick skillet. Heat skillet over medium heat.
Drop rounded tablespoons of batter into skillet.
Cook until golden and crisp on bottom, 2 to 3 minutes.
Turn over to brown other side.
Keep warm.
Repeat with remaining batter and oil.

title: sinful salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine jello and boiling water.
Stir until jello is completely dissolved.
Cool.
Add bananas, pecans, strawberries and pineapple to jello; stir to combine; divide in half.

title: brown rack cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and coffee. Then add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 hour and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: judy's poppy seed cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Turn out when cool and glaze with the glaze.

title: cherry winks cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except crushed corn flakes.
Make into small balls; roll in corn flakes.
Decorate with 1/2 or 1/4 cherry.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: broccoli dip(can be served over rice)
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Heat thoroughly.

title: krunchy kiss kookies
directions: Mix syrup and brown sugar in a pot.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Mix peanut butter and vanilla.
Add rice cereal and corn flakes.
Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Shape into balls and press chocolate kisses in the centers.

title: sloppy toms
directions: Brown turkey and onion until meat is no longer pink.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally.
Serve on whole wheat rolls.
This is a super alternative to red meat.
A healthy choice.

title: onioned potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cut each in 3 or 4 lengthwise slices.
Blend butter and soup mix.
Spread on slices.
Put on squares of foil and wrap tightly.
Bake until done, turning once, on the grill or right on top of coals, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: wedding cakes
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Chill one hour.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
When cool, roll cookies in confectioners sugar.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream the sugar and cream cheese.
Add fruit and pecans; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix to a thick paste.
Drop by teaspoon into boiling soup.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together; place in greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet and sour mostaccioli salad
directions: Coat noodles with oil.	Combine remaining ingredients.	Mix and combine with noodles.
Stir every 10 to 15 minutes for first two hours. Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: yum-yum
directions: Mix cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on crust. Mix pudding and milk.
Spread on top of second layer.
Add rest of Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, soup and cheese sauce in a 2 qt. casserole dish. Mix water, margarine and stuffing; spoon over green beans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
tags: Stove Top Stuffing Mix for Chicken

title: hot caramel rolls
directions: Butter Bundt pan well.
Place frozen bread rolls in pan.
Pour pudding on top.
Sprinkle nut halves on top (some will fall through).
Melt butter and brown sugar.
Bring to boil.
Add more nuts if desired.
Pour over rolls and let set overnight (no breeze), covered with wax paper.
In morning remove wax paper. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn out on plate and enjoy.

title: chewy ginger cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream shortening and 1 cup sugar (mix by hand). Add egg, molasses and vanilla. Mix well. Combine dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture. Mix well. Roll into 1-inch balls. Roll in remaining sugar. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown. Let sit 1 minute on baking sheet after taking out of oven. Cool on wire racks.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook beans or peas; drain and cool.
Combine everything, except noodles.
Add noodles just before serving.
You may also wait and add torn lettuce with the noodles for a crispy salad.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop broccoli and cauliflower heads, green pepper, onion, seed and chop tomatoes and cucumbers.
Combine in large bowl; sprinkle with Italian dressing.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix well all ingredients as listed.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can change by adding 1/2 cup grated cheese and jalapeno peppers.

title: corn pie
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes.
Mix cornbread mix, corn, egg yolks and cheese.
Add tomato-onion mixture. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes 2 large or 4 small loafs.

title: pot of luck main dish
directions: Mix leaf, egg, bread crumbs, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into meat balls.
In saucepan, brown meat balls in shortening; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes about 7 cups.
Very good reheated.

title: egg drop soup(chinese appetizer)
directions: Put the chicken, water chestnuts, broth and 2 cups water into saucepan and bring to a boil.
Mix the cornstarch and 3 tablespoons of water and add to the soup, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add beaten eggs in a slow steady stream to boiling soup, stirring constantly.
Continue to stir until eggs are set.
Serve piping hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Fold in bananas.
Pour into a prepared tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Makes 20 servings.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Blend celery soup with water.
Reserve 1/4 cup soup mixture. Combine remaining soup mixture with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, parsley and salt.
Shape into balls, 1-inch in diameter. Brown in shortening in large skillet.
Add reserved soup mixture and dill pickle.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stew
directions: Wipe pieces of beef with damp cloth and roll in flour.
Brown in fat in heavy kettle or saucepan.
Add water, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cover tightly; cook over low heat until almost tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add prepared onions, carrots and potatoes.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes longer.
Just before vegetables are tender, add green peas and cook 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: red raspberry or strawberry glaze pie
directions: Cook berries, water, sugar and cornstarch until thick and clear.
Cool.
Pour half of sauce in baked pie shell.
Add rest of berries and rest of sauce on top of berries.
Cool.
Serve with whipped topping if desired.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Dot bottom of 9 x 9 x 2 baking dish with butter.
In a bowl mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour on butter and spoon fruit over all, allowing space for dough to bubble up. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter, mix with flour in a baking dish. Add eggs, milk sugar, vanilla and corn; stir to combine. Put pats of butter on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake 3 hours at 350°. Stir occasionally.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.

title: surprise meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, egg and spices. Flatten thick on aluminum foil.
Spread cheese on this, saving 1/2 cup.
Peel meat up from foil with cheese inside.
Discard foil.
Place in baking dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish for one hour at 350°.

title: mrs. r. f. urie and mrs. john maxcy's banana cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs; beat until fluffy, adding dry ingredients with milk and banana pulp.
Bake about 40 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.
Use any desired frosting.

title: cranberry chip bars
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla, then flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir until blended.
Fold in cranberries, nuts and chips.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(An old Girl Scout recipe.)

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and cut off bones.
Place chicken in shallow pan (9 x 13-inches).
Mix chicken broth and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
(Add vegetables if wanted.)
Mix flour, milk and melted margarine together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 425° for about 35 minutes or until brown.

title: super chocolate chunk oat cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, vanilla and 1 egg until light and fluffy. Add flour, oats, soda and salt and stir until well blended.
Stir in chocolate pieces (cut into 1/2 chunks) and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool 2 minutes, then remove and cool on rack.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Turn on oven and set at 350°.
Sprinkle pork chops with 1/4 teaspoon salt and a few grains of pepper.
Brown chops on both sides in 10-inch skillet over medium heat in one tablespoon hot shortening.
Drain off drippings.
Pour around chops a mixture of 1 can cream of mushroom soup, evaporated milk and water.
Bake at 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Stir gravy well.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and place in casserole dish. Mix last 2 ingredients together and sprinkle this topping over the casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: ground meat drumsticks
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into four patties shaped like chicken drumsticks.
Use metal or wooden skewers for "bones". Roll in fine bread crumbs and fry in 2 tablespoons of oil until brown on all sides.
Cover.
Turn down heat and cook 15 to 20 minutes more.
Heat a can of cream of chicken soup and 1/2 can water.
Add 2 tablespoons chopped parsley.
Serve in a gravy boat on the side with the crispy drumsticks and cooked wide noodles.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables and drain.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
On stove, combine 1 can celery soup and small jar of Cheez Whiz, until melted.
Pour over vegetables and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cook diced potatoes until soft done.
Drain off liquid.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well.

title: cheese grits(makes 4 servings)
directions: Add 3 1/2 cups water to the top of a medium double boiler. Place over high heat; bring to a boil.
Gradually add grits, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly for 5 minutes.
Add 1 inch water to the bottom of the double boiler; place over medium-high heat and bring to a simmer.
Place upper half of boiler on top.
Cook, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: grandma stafford's pear preserves
directions: Slice pears thin.
Combine with sugar and cloves.
Simmer until thick.
Let set in pot overnight and put in jars.

title: apple-cherry nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Beat sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.

title: tomato basil soup
directions: Combine tomatoes and juice in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Simmer 30 minutes.
In a blender or food processor, combine the tomato mixture and 12 to 14 basil leaves.
Do this in several small batches.
Process until smooth.

title: a good dip
directions: This dip will keep for 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix together egg yolks and milk in medium saucepan.
Stir dry ingredients together and add slowly to this mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
(This takes about 8 minutes.)
Stir in vanilla and set aside to cool.
Pour into cooled pie shell and chill.

title: holly fried potatoes
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients in a plastic bag.
Shake potatoes in mixture.
Place on a cookie sheet and pour margarine over.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cover with foil.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes about 1/4 inch thick.
Arrange potatoes and onions in microwave dish.
Stir together water and barbecue sauce. Pour over vegetables.
Cover; cook on 100% power for 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes and onions are tender.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo to the soft ball stage.
Add peanuts and margarine.
Cook until it starts to turn brown.
Add soda and vanilla.
Stir until it quits foaming.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: easy casserole bread(low-fat)
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 1 cup flour and yeast.
In saucepan, heat water and sugar until warm (120°).
Add to dry mixture.
Beat at low speed 30 seconds.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, or with dough hook, stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Place into lightly greased bowl; turn once to grease surface.
Cover; let rise until double (1 hour). Punch down.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.

title: sweetheart cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually and yolk of 1 egg, creaming well.
Add flour and knead.
Chill several hours.
Form into tiny balls, about the size of marbles, and place on greased cookie sheet.
Make depression in each
center.
Fill hollow with jam. "Currant or raspberry is good." Bake in moderate oven, 350°, until very light brown.
"May be rolled in powdered sugar while still warm."

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix the dry ingredients and stir in the water.
Boil until the sauce thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Serve hot or cold.

title: bread machine rolls mix
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients. Store in a resealable plastic bag. Yield: 1 batch (3 1/3 cups).

title: hot salsa and cheese dip
directions: Cube Velveeta and mix with salsa.
Microwave, stirring occasionally until smooth.
Serve hot with chips, crackers or vegetables.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Add Cool Whip.
Put layer of crackers in dish, then spread with pudding mixture.
Makes two layers.
Then place crackers on top layer.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Chill.

title: russian easter bread(kulich)
directions: Place 1 cup flour in a large bowl, scald cream and blend into flour.
Cool just to lukewarm, stir in yeast.
Beat 1/2 cup sugar and salt into egg yolks.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding the remaining sugar.
Fold stiffly beaten egg whites into yeast-egg yolk mixture.
Place bowl over pan of hot but not boiling water and let mixture rise until light and full of bubbles.
Stir down.
Beat the soft butter and add remaining flour gradually using just enough to make the dough firm enough to be kneaded.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Whirl artichoke hearts in blender and add mayonnaise and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with small chunks of French bread, bread sticks or crackers.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Boil raisins, Crisco and water for 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken
directions: Cut cooked chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute bell peppers and onion.
Add thawed broccoli and cheese.
Let melt.
Add tomatoes, then other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in a dish and bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: new york special cookie
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler and heat. Stir until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Add graham crackers, coconut and nuts.
Spread in jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Cool in refrigerator.

title: brook's shrimp casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender and put into Pyrex dish.
Saute shrimp in 1 stick butter or margarine until pink and pour them (plus butter) over noodles; spread evenly. Combine next 5 ingredients and spread over shrimp-noodle mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread cheese over top. Bake 5 more minutes or until cheese melts.

title: tomato-cheese pie
directions: Combine cheeses, onion, mushrooms and salmon.
Spoon into shell.
Arrange tomato wedges over filling.
Sprinkle with herbs, green onions, salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes before serving.

title: buttermilk cake with fresh grated coconut frosting
directions: Put all ingredients into mixing bowl (except eggs).
Beat until creamy, then add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Divide batter into two cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking pan. Mix apricots and mustard.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake covered for 40 minutes at 350°.
Baste and bake 10 more minutes, uncovered.
Yields 2 servings (easily doubled or tripled).
Never make just 2 servings of this, you'll want leftovers.
Has 200 calories, 4 g fat.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, chicken broth and onion soup mix in baking dish. Arrange chicken on top of mixture.
Put dabs of margarine on top. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: fruit punch
